1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bc4 Nf6 4. d3 h6 5. O-O d6 6. c3 g6 7. d4 Qe7 8. Re1 Bg7 9. h3 {(D) } O-O $1 10. Nbd2 Bd7 {(D) } 11. Nf1 Rae8 $5 12. Ng3 $5 Kh8 (12... Qd8 13. Bb3 a6 14. Bc2 Nh7 15. Be3 h5 16. Qd2 Qf6 17. Kh2 Bc8 18. Rad1 Kh8 19. Ne2 Qe7 $11 {Nielsen,P-Nataf,I/Reykjavik 2004} 20. Ng5 {is not bad either:} Nxg5 21. Bxg5 f6 22. Be3 f5 23. Bg5 Bf6 24. Bxf6+ Rxf6 25. f4 Qg7 26. fxe5 dxe5 27. exf5 Bxf5 28. Bxf5 Rxf5 29. Ng3 Rff8 30. d5 Nd8 31. Ne4 Rf4 32. Qe3 Ref8 33. Nc5 {½-½ Jirovsky,M-Rasik,V/Czech Rep. 1993} e4 34. Nxe4 Qe5 35. g3 R4f7 36. Kg2 Kg7 37. Qd2 c6 38. c4 cxd5 39. cxd5 $14 {Pogosian,M-Mokriy,A/Minsk 2006} h4 $5 40. gxh4 Qh5 41. Qc3+ Kg8 42. Qg3) 13. Bd3 (13. a4 Qd8 14. a5 $17 {Jacobsen,B-Hvenekilde,J/Aarhus 1981} {This looks better than White's main alternatives: a)} exd4 15. cxd4 d5 16. exd5 Rxe1+ 17. Qxe1 Ne7 18. Qb4 Bc8 19. a6 Nfxd5 20. Qb3 bxa6 21. Bxa6 $15 {Hassan,A-Maslak,K/Olomouc 2005} Be6 22. Bc4 Nc6 23. Ne4 Qb8 $13 {Jussupow,A-Gulko,B/Reykjavik 1990} {b)} 24. Nc5 Qxb3 25. Bxb3 Nxd4 26. Nxd4 Bxd4 27. Bxh6 Bxc5 28. Bxd5 Bxd5 29. Ra5 Bb6 30. Rxd5 Re8 31. Kf1 Kh7 32. Bd2 Re6 $13 33. Bc3 $2 f5 34. Rd7+ Kg8 35. g4 fxg4 36. hxg4 Kf8 {Szmetan,J-Valerga,D/Argentina 2000} 37. g5 $15 Re7 38. Rd3 Ke8 39. Rh3 Re4 40. Rh7 Rf4 41. Rg7 $15 {Granda Zuniga,J-Mendoza Nieto,J/Burriana 1990} {A critical continuation is} Bxf2 {although Black seems to be doing fine after} 42. Ke2 Bd4) 13... Nh7 14. d5 Nd8 $5 15. Qc2 h5 16. Bd2 $2 h4 $1 17. Nf1 f5 18. c4 c5 $1 19. b4 cxb4 $1 {The coming 20...a7 forced White to resign.} 20. Bxb4 b6 $1 21. Qc1 Nb7 {A must is} 22. Qa3 a5 23. Bd2 Nc5 24. Rad1 Rf7 $44 25. N1h2 $2 fxe4 26. Bxe4 Bf5 27. Bxf5 gxf5 28. Rb1 Qd8 $17 29. Be3 e4 30. Bxc5 (30. Nd2) 30... bxc5 31. Nd2 $11 Rg8 32. Ndf1 Bd4 33. Kh1 Qg5 34. g4 $11 {Of course Black can immediately play} hxg3 35. fxg3 Qh4 36. Rb8 Qxh3 37. Rxg8+ Kxg8 38. Qxa5 Nf6 39. Qd8+ Kg7 40. Qxd6 Rb7 41. Re2 Rb1 $11 {Jasnikowski,Z-Malisauskas,V/Katowice 1993} 42. Qf4 $6 Nh5 43. Qc7+ Kg6 44. Qd6+ Kg5 45. Rf2 Rxf1+ 0-1


