1. d4 {Grivas,E} Nf6 2. c4 g6 3. Nc3 d5 4. Nf3 Bg7 5. Bg5 Ne4 6. Bh4 Nxc3 7. bxc3 dxc4 8. Qa4+ Qd7 9. Qxc4 b6 10. e3 Ba6 11. Qb3 Bxf1 12. Kxf1 O-O 13. Ke2 c5 14. dxc5 Na6 15. Rhd1 (15. cxb6 $6 Nc5 16. Qc4 axb6 17. Rhd1 Qb7 $1 $15) 15... Qb7 $2 {[This is surely a mistake, losing an important tempo.]} 16. c6 Qxc6 (16... Qc7 17. h3 $1 {preserves the h-pawn, avoiding the nasty 18...xh2!, as in Haba,P-Ilincic,Z/Prague 1989.}) 17. Bxe7 Rfe8 (17... Rfc8 18. Rac1 $16 Bxc3 $2 19. Rxc3 Qxc3 20. Rd8+ $18) 18. Ba3 (18. Bb4 $2 Nxb4 19. Qxb4 Bxc3 20. Rac1 Qxf3+ $19) 18... Rad8 19. Rac1 $16 Nc7 20. c4 Ne6 21. Kf1 Qe4 22. Rd5 Rc8 23. Qd3 Qxd3+ 24. Rxd3 Rc7 25. Nd2 f5 26. Rb1 Bf8 27. Bxf8 Kxf8 28. h3 Nc5 29. Rd4 h5 30. h4 Ke7 31. g3 Rec8 32. Ke2 {[White's advantage in this endgame is obvious, although he managed to misplace it!]} Rc6 33. Rb5 Ne6 34. Rd3 Nc5 35. Rd5 Kf6 36. Rb2 R8c7 37. Rb4 Na6 38. Rb2 Nc5 39. Rc2 Rc8 40. Rd4 Ke7 41. f3 Ne6 42. Rd5 Nc7 43. Rd3 Nb5 44. a4 Nd6 45. Rd4 Rc5 46. g4 $2 (46. Kd3 Nf7 47. Kc3 Ra5 48. Kb3 $16) 46... hxg4 47. fxg4 fxg4 $2 (47... Rh8 48. Nf3 Ra5 49. Ra2 Ne4 50. Ra3 Kf6 $14) 48. Rxg4 $16 Kf7 49. Ne4 Nxe4 50. Rxe4 Ra5 51. Ra2 Rd8 52. Ra1 Rd6 53. Kf3 Rd2 54. Rd4 Rh2 55. Ra3 Rc2 56. Ke4 Rh2 57. Kd3 Ke6 58. Ra1 Rg2 59. Re4+ Kd6 60. Kc3 Re5 $2 (60... Kc6 $16) 61. Rxe5 $2 (61. Rd1+ $1 Ke6 62. Rxe5+ Kxe5 63. Rd7 $18) 61... Kxe5 62. a5 Rg3 63. Kd3 Kd6 64. axb6 axb6 65. Ra8 (65. Rb1 Kc6 66. Rb5 Rh3 67. Rg5 Rxh4 68. Rxg6+ Kc5 69. Rg5+ Kc6 70. e4 $16) 65... Rg4 66. Rf8 $2 (66. Rh8 Kc5 67. h5 gxh5 68. Rxh5+ Kd6 69. Rd5+ Kc6 70. e4 $16) 66... Rxh4 67. Rf6+ Kc5 68. Rxg6 Rxc4 $1 69. Rxb6 Kxb6 70. Kxc4 1/2-1/2


