1. d4 {Efstratios Grivas} Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 d5 4. Nc3 Bb4 5. cxd5 exd5 6. Bg5 Nbd7 7. Rc1 c5 8. dxc5 Qa5 $6 ({I do not think that the text move helps Black; nor do the following alternatives: a)} 8... O-O $6 9. a3 Bxc3+ 10. Rxc3 h6 11. Bxf6 Nxf6 12. Qd4 Ne4 13. Rc1 Qa5+ 14. Qb4 Qxb4+ 15. axb4 a5 16. b5 Bd7 17. Nd4 $16 {Vallejo Pons,F-Aronian,L/Khanty Mansiysk 2005.}) ({b)} 8... h6 $6 9. Bxf6 Nxf6 $2 (9... Qxf6 10. a3 $16) 10. Qa4+ {1-0 Banikas,H-Kalaitzoglou,P/Kallithea 2008.}) ({c)} 8... Bxc3+ $6 9. Rxc3 Qa5 10. Nd2 Qxa2 11. Qc1 $1 (11. Re3+ Kf8 12. Bf4 Qxb2 13. Bd6+ Kg8 14. g3 $44 {Kuijf,M-Brenninkmeijer,J/Netherlands 1992}) 11... Qa4 12. Re3+ Kf8 13. Ra3 $16 {Komarov,D-Delanoy,A/Le Touquet 1993.}) ({But by choosing the 'obvious' d)} 8... Nxc5 {alternative, Black can fight:} 9. Qd4 Bxc3+ (9... a5 10. Bxf6 Qxf6 11. Qxf6 gxf6 12. e3 (12. a3 Nb3 13. Rd1 Bxc3+ 14. bxc3 Be6 15. Nd4 a4 16. e3 {½-½ Lalic,B-Jobava,B/Sibenik 2007}) 12... O-O 13. Bb5 Ne4 14. Ke2 Bxc3 (14... Nxc3+ 15. bxc3 Be7 16. Rb1 $14) 15. bxc3 Bg4 16. h3 Be6 (16... Bxf3+ $6 17. gxf3 Nd6 18. Ba4 $16) 17. Nd4 $14) 10. Qxc3 (10. Rxc3 $5 Nce4 (10... Ne6 $2 11. Bxf6 Nxd4 12. Bxd8 Nxf3+ 13. Rxf3 Kxd8 14. Rxf7 $16) 11. Bxf6 Qxf6 (11... Nxf6 12. e3 O-O 13. Bd3 Re8 14. O-O Ne4 15. Rc2 $16 {Cvitan,O-Soffer,R/Biel 1990}) 12. Qxf6 Nxf6 13. e3 $14 {½-½ Cebalo, M-Braga,F/Reggio Emilia 1991}) 10... Nce4 11. Bxf6 Nxf6 (11... Qxf6 12. Qxf6 Nxf6 13. Nd4 $14 {Cvitan,O-Braga,F/Reggio Emilia 1991}) 12. e3 O-O 13. Be2 Ne4 {and it transposes to Grivas,E-Gelashvili,T/Kocaeli 2008.}) 9. Bd2 $1 ({A strong retreat as White has not played e3 yet.} 9. a3 {is not great:} Bxc3+ 10. Rxc3 Ne4 11. Bd2 Ndxc5 (11... Nxc3 $6 12. Bxc3 Qxc5 13. Bxg7 Rg8 14. Bd4 (14. Bc3 Nb6 15. g3 Be6 16. Bg2 O-O-O 17. O-O $44 {Calderin,R-Pazos,P/Cienfuegos 1991}) 14... Qd6 15. g3 Nb6 16. Bg2 Bf5 17. O-O $44 {Donoso,C-Endara,N/Pichincha 1962}) 12. Rc1 Nxd2 13. Qxd2 Qxd2+ 14. Nxd2 b6 $1 15. e3 Ke7 16. b4 Ne6 $11 {Navara,D-Carlsen,M/Wijk aan Zee 2006.}) 9... Bxc5 (9... Nxc5 $2 10. a3 $18 {.}) 10. e3 Qd8 (10... Qb6 11. Na4 Qd6 12. Nxc5 Nxc5 13. Qc2 Nfe4 14. Nd4 a6 15. f3 Nxd2 16. Qxc5 Qxc5 17. Rxc5 Nxf1 18. Rxf1 $16 {Magerramov,E-Goldin,V/Moscow 1991.}) 11. Qb3 $1 ({Better than} 11. Bd3 O-O 12. O-O a6 13. Qc2 Ba7 14. Ne2 $14 {Arsovic,G-Ivanovic,B/Herceg Novi 2007.}) 11... O-O (11... Qb6 12. Nxd5 Nxd5 (12... Qxb3 13. Nxf6+ Nxf6 14. axb3 $18) 13. Qxd5 O-O 14. Bd3 Qd6 15. Qxd6 Bxd6 16. Ke2 $18 {Goldstern,F-Ruefenacht,M/Switzerland 1993.}) 12. Nxd5 Bd6 (12... b6 13. Be2 (13. Bc4 Ne4 14. Qc2 $16 {Huzman,A-Dizdar,G/Baku 1988}) 13... Ne4 14. O-O Nxd2 15. Nxd2 Bb7 16. Rfd1 $16 {Lobron,E-Gulko,B/Vienna 1991.}) 13. Nxf6+ Qxf6 (13... Nxf6 14. Bb4 $16 {.}) 14. Bc3 {White has won a precious pawn and Black cannot show any serious compensation.} Ne5 $6 ({Exchanging pieces when a pawn down cannot be the right policy for Black. he had to play} 14... Qe7 15. Qc2 Nc5 16. Bc4 $16 {.}) 15. Nxe5 Bxe5 16. Bxe5 Qxe5 17. Bc4 Bf5 18. O-O Be4 19. f3 Bc6 20. Rfd1 Rae8 21. e4 Qc5+ 22. Kh1 Qf2 23. Rc2 Qh4 24. Rcd2 h6 25. Bd5 Bxd5 26. Rxd5 $18 {The game is theoretically over. White need only 'perform' some basic technique.} Re7 27. Qc3 Rfe8 28. Kg1 b6 29. a3 Qf4 30. Qd2 Qxd2 31. R1xd2 Rc7 32. Kf2 Rec8 33. h4 Rc5 34. Ke3 h5 35. Rd8+ Kh7 36. R8d7 R8c7 37. Kf4 g6 38. e5 Kh6 39. g3 a5 40. Rxc7 Rxc7 41. Rd6 b5 42. Rd5 Rb7 43. b4 axb4 44. axb4 Rb6 45. Ke4 Kg7 46. f4 Kf8 47. Rd6 Rb7 48. f5 Rc7 (48... gxf5+ 49. Kxf5 Rb8 50. Kg5 $18 {.}) 49. fxg6 fxg6 50. Rxg6 Rc4+ 51. Kf5 Rxb4 52. Rg5 1-0


