1. d4 {Efstratios Grivas} Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 d5 4. Nc3 Bb4 5. cxd5 exd5 6. Bg5 h6 7. Bxf6 {Ribli: 'This move leads to simple play, in which White possess the initiative.' Ribli: 'Dieser Zug führt zu einfachem Spiel, in dem Weiß die Inititive innehat.'} Qxf6 8. Qb3 Qd6 ({Of course, in such an early opening position, Black can try many options: a)} 8... Bxc3+ 9. Qxc3 (9. bxc3 c6 10. e3 O-O 11. c4 (11. Bd3 b6 12. O-O Be6 13. Ne5 c5 14. Be2 Rd8 15. f4 $14 c4 $6 16. Qa3 Bf5 17. Bh5 g6 18. Bf3 h5 19. Rae1 $16 {Cramling,P-Vallin,G/France 2001}) (11. a4 Nd7 12. Rc1 Qd6 13. c4 dxc4 14. Bxc4 Nb6 15. O-O Nxc4 16. Qxc4 Be6 17. Qc5 Rfd8 18. Qxd6 Rxd6 19. Ne5 f6 20. Nd3 Kf7 21. Rc3 Rb8 22. f3 Ke7 23. Kf2 Kd8 24. a5 Kc7 25. Rfc1 $14 {Rakhmanov,A-Provotorov,I/Voronezh 2007}) 11... dxc4 12. Bxc4 Nd7 13. a4 Nb6 14. Be2 Be6 15. Qa3 Nd5 16. O-O a5 17. Rfc1 Nb4 18. Ne5 $14 {Cobo Arteaga,E-Rossetto,H/Helsinki 1952}) 9... c6 10. e3 O-O 11. Be2 Qg6 12. O-O Bh3 13. Ne1 Nd7 14. Kh1 Bf5 15. Nd3 Qd6 16. b4 $14 {Butnorius,A-Sarakauskas,G/Kaunas 2001.}) ({b)} 8... Nc6 {Ribli: 'With the text move Black deprives himself of the chance to play c7-c5, and at the same time the knight is not particularly well placed on c6.' Ribli: 'Mit dem Textzug verbaut sich Schwarz die Möglichkeit zu c7-c5, zudem steht der Springer nicht sonderlich gut auf c6.'} 9. e3 (9. Qxd5 $5 {Taking the pawn immediately is also worth considering. Das sofortige Schlagen des Bauern kommt auch in Betracht.} Be6 10. Qb5 O-O-O $44) 9... O-O (9... Be6 10. Bb5 Bxc3+ 11. Qxc3 Bd7 12. Qc5 (12. O-O O-O 13. Rfc1 Bg4 14. Ne1 Bd7 15. Qb3 Qd6 16. Bxc6 Bxc6 17. Nd3 $14 {Shishkin,V-Ginzburg,M/Polanica Zdroj 2001}) 12... Qd6 13. Bxc6 Bxc6 14. Rc1 Qxc5 15. Rxc5 f6 16. Kd2 a5 17. Rhc1 Kf7 18. Ne1 Rhd8 19. Nd3 Rd6 20. R5c3 g5 21. Ra3 Ra6 22. Rc5 b5 23. Nb4 {1-0 Ivanov,I-Manthe,B/Chicago 1989}) (9... Qd6 10. Bd3 Bg4 11. O-O Bxf3 12. gxf3 O-O-O 13. Rfc1 a6 14. Na4 $14 {Epishin,V-Tal,M/Tallinn 1988}) (9... Qg6 10. Be2 O-O 11. O-O Bxc3 12. Qxc3 Qd6 13. Rfc1 Bg4 14. h3 Bh5 15. Qc5 $14 {Baikov,V-Moiseenko,A/Moscow 1996}) 10. Qxd5 {White takes the pawn, after which Black does have seomething of an initiative. But the white centre with the pawns on e3-d4 is so strong that White need have no fear. (Ribli). Weiß nimmt den Bauern, wonach Schwarz in der Tat etwas Initiative bekommt. Das weiße Zentrum mit den Bauern auf e3-d4 ist aber so stark, dass Weiß keine Angst zu haben braucht (Ribli).} (10. Be2 $5 Qd6 11. O-O Be6 12. Rfc1 Na5 13. Qc2 c6 14. Na4 $14 {Ivanov,I-Murey,J/New York 1983}) 10... Be6 (10... Re8 11. Be2 Qg6 (11... Be6 12. Qb5 a6 13. Qd3 Rad8 14. O-O $16 {Cramling,D-Valkesalmi,K/Groningen 1978 Black has active piece play but that is not sufficient compensation for the pawn. (Ribli) Schwarz hat aktive Figurenspiel, aber das ist keine ausreichende Kompensation für den Bauern (Ribli).}) 12. O-O Be6 13. Qb5 Bh3 (13... Rad8 $2 14. Bd3 f5 15. Rfd1 $16 {Maric,A-Randjelovic,D/Herceg Novi 2005}) 14. Nh4 Qf6 15. Qh5 $16 {Hort,V-Sofrevski,J/Skopje 1968}) 11. Qb5 (11. Qh5 Rfd8 12. Be2 Rd5 13. Qh4 g5 14. Qg3 $14 {Ponceleusz,B-Kwiatkowski,A/Warsaw 2008}) 11... Qg6 (11... a6 12. Qd3 Na5 13. Be2 $14 {Roessel,F-Filipowicz,A/Varna 1958}) 12. O-O-O Bxc3 13. bxc3 Bxa2 14. d5 Ne7 15. c4 Qb6 16. Nd4 $14 {Horvath,J-Bokros,A/Budapest 2001.}) ({c)} 8... Qb6 $5 {(a rather unexplored move which is difficult to meet)} 9. e3 {and now:} (9. a3 Ba5 10. Qc2 Bf5 11. Qa4+ (11. Qxf5 Qxb2 12. Rb1 Qxc3+ 13. Kd1 O-O 14. e3 Qxa3 15. Qxd5 Nc6 16. Bc4 Nb4 17. Qf5 b5 18. Qxb5 Na2 19. Bxa2 Qxa2 20. Rb2 Qa1+ 21. Rb1 Qa2 22. Rb2 Qa1+ {½-½ Portisch,L-Khenkin,I/Saint Vincent 2005}) (11. Qc1 Qb3 12. Nd2 Bxc3 13. bxc3 Qb6 14. e3 O-O $11 {Hauchard,A-Dizdar,G/Debrecen 1992}) 11... Bd7 {½-½ Gostisa,L-Dizdar,G/Celje 2003}) {c3)} 9... O-O ({c1)} 9... c6 10. Bd3 Nd7 {(½-½ Kempinski,R-Wojtkiewicz,A/Brzeg Dolny 1996 ;} (10... Be6 11. O-O Nd7 12. Na4 Qa5 13. a3 Be7 14. Qxb7 Nb6 15. Nxb6 axb6 16. Ne5 {1-0 Paschall,W-Furdzik,R/Stratton Mountain 2003}) 11. O-O Bd6 12. Qc2 Nf6 13. Rab1 (13. Rac1 Be6 14. Na4 Qc7 15. Nc5 Bg4 16. Ne5 $14 {Lund,E-Nilsson,N/Copenhagen 1994}) 13... a5 14. Bf5 $14 {Ristic,N-Vasiljevic,D/Zlatibor 1989.}) ({c2)} 9... Ba5 10. Bd3 (10. Qxb6 {½-½ Wojtkiewicz,A-Dizdar,G/Hamburg 1993}) 10... Be6 11. Qc2 $14 {.}) 10. Bd3 c6 11. O-O Bd6 12. Qc2 Nd7 13. e4 $5 (13. a3 a5 (13... Nf6 14. b4 a6 15. h3 Re8 16. Rab1 Re7 17. Rfc1 Bd7 18. Na4 Qc7 19. Nc5 Rae8 20. a4 Ne4 21. Nxd7 Qxd7 22. b5 {½-½ Hebert,J-Kovacevic,V/Toronto 1989}) 14. Rfe1 Nf6 15. Rac1 Re8 16. h3 Qd8 17. Bf5 Bxf5 18. Qxf5 Ne4 19. Nxe4 dxe4 20. Nd2 g6 21. Qg4 Kh7 $11 {Pirc,V-Kostic,B/Zagreb 1946}) 13... dxe4 14. Nxe4 Be7 15. Rfe1 Qd8 16. Rad1 $14 {.}) 9. a3 Bxc3+ ({White retains some advantage even after} 9... Ba5 10. Qa4+ (10. e3 c6 11. Bd3 O-O 12. Qc2 Qe7 13. O-O Bc7 14. Rac1 Rd8 15. Bh7+ Kh8 16. Bf5 $14 {Gavrilov,A-Khismatullin,D/Zvenigorod 2008}) 10... Nc6 11. b4 Bb6 12. e3 O-O 13. Be2 Ne7 14. O-O c6 15. b5 c5 16. dxc5 Bxc5 17. Rfd1 $14 {Kasparov,G-Kupreichik,V/Minsk 1978.}) 10. Qxc3 O-O ({The other options are quite similar: a)} 10... Bf5 11. e3 Nd7 12. Be2 O-O 13. O-O a5 14. b4 axb4 15. axb4 c6 (15... Rfc8 16. Rfc1 Nf8 17. Ne5 Ne6 18. b5 $14 {Slipak,S-Van Riemsdijk,H/Vicente Lopez 2000}) 16. Rfc1 Rfc8 17. b5 (17. h3 Nf6 18. Nd2 Qd8 19. Bf1 Ne8 {½-½ Bruzon Bautista,L-Onischuk,A/Buenos Aires 2005}) 17... Rxa1 18. Qxa1 c5 19. dxc5 Nxc5 20. Nd4 $14 {Mchedlishvili,M-Zelcic,R/Bled 2002.}) ({b)} 10... c6 11. e3 Bf5 12. Be2 O-O 13. O-O Nd7 14. b4 $14 {Shulman,Y-Perelshteyn,E/Tulsa 2008.}) 11. b4 $5 (11. e3 a5 12. Bd3 Be6 13. O-O Nd7 14. b4 $14 {½-½ Chuchelov,V-Izoria,Z/Aghia Pelagia 2004.}) 11... Bf5 12. e3 Nd7 13. Be2 Nf6 14. O-O Rfe8 (14... Ne4 15. Qb2 Bg4 16. b5 $14 {. In general, in this simplified position White has a plan: minority attack. The question is what is Black's plan?}) 15. Rfc1 Re7 16. Qc5 $1 {By exchanging queens Black is restrained by a potentional attack on the white king.} Qe6 (16... Ne4 17. Qxd6 Nxd6 (17... cxd6 18. h3 g6 19. Ra2 $14) 18. b5 $14 {.}) 17. Nd2 g5 18. b5 h5 19. a4 Kg7 20. a5 b6 $6 (20... h4 21. a6 b6 22. Qc6 $14 {.}) 21. Qc6 Rc8 22. axb6 $6 (22. Qxe6 Bxe6 23. Bd3 $16 {.}) 22... cxb6 23. Qxe6 Bxe6 24. Rxc8 Bxc8 25. Rc1 Bb7 26. Nf3 $1 g4 $6 (26... Ne4 27. Ne5 f6 28. Nd3 h4 29. Nb4 $14 {.}) 27. Nh4 Kf8 28. h3 $1 g3 (28... gxh3 29. gxh3 Rd7 30. Nf5 $16 {.}) 29. Nf5 gxf2+ 30. Kxf2 Rd7 31. Ng3 Ke7 (31... h4 32. Nf5 {.}) 32. Nxh5 Ne4+ 33. Ke1 f5 34. Bd3 Nd6 35. g4 $16 fxg4 36. hxg4 Kf8 37. g5 Re7 38. Kd2 Bc8 39. Rc6 Re6 40. g6 Bd7 41. Rc7 Be8 42. Nf4 Rf6 43. Nxd5 Rf2+ 44. Ke1 Rg2 45. Nf4 1-0


