1. d4 {Grivas,E} Nf6 2. c4 g6 3. Nc3 d5 4. Bg5 Bg7 5. Nf3 Ne4 6. Bh4 Nxc3 7. bxc3 dxc4 8. Qa4+ Qd7 9. Qxc4 b6 10. e3 Ba6 11. Qb3 Bxf1 12. Kxf1 O-O 13. Ke2 c5 14. dxc5 {[After a lot of recent research I am not sure anymore that this is the right way to a stable advantage.]} Na6 15. Rad1 {[A new try (at that moment). The disadvantage is of course the poor "coordination" of the white rooks.]} Qc7 16. c6 Nc5 ({Black should avoid the immediate} 16... Qxc6 $6 17. Bxe7 Rfe8 (17... Rfc8 18. Rd3) 18. Ba3 $1 (18. Bb4 Qb5+ 19. Rd3 Rad8 20. Rhd1 Rxd3 21. Rxd3 Rd8 22. Ne1 Nc7 (22... Rxd3 $2 23. Nxd3 Qh5+ 24. Kd2 Qxh2 25. Qa4 $1 Nxb4 26. Qe8+ Bf8 27. Ne5 Qh6 28. Qxf7+ Kh8 29. Qe8 Kg7 30. Qd7+ Kg8 31. Qe6+ Kg7 32. a3 $1 $16) 23. c4 Rxd3 24. Nxd3 Qh5+ $11) 18... Qxc3 19. Rd7 $1 $14 {.}) (16... Nb8 $5 {is another interesting try:} 17. Rd3 (17. Qd5 Nxc6 18. Nd4 Nxd4+ (18... Bxd4 $2 19. cxd4 Nb4 20. Qb3 $16) 19. cxd4 e6 20. Qb3 Rac8 $11) (17. Bg3 Qxc6 18. Qd5 Rc8 $11) 17... Nxc6 18. Bg3 (18. Rhd1 Rad8 19. Qc4 Rxd3 20. Rxd3 Qb7 $11) 18... Qb7 (18... e5 $6 19. Rhd1 Na5 20. Qb5 Qc4 21. Qxc4 Nxc4 22. Rd7 $14) 19. Rhd1 Rad8 $11) 17. Qc4 e6 $6 ({Best of course is} 17... Rfc8 $1) 18. Nd4 e5 ({Now it is too late for} 18... Rfc8 19. Bg3 $1 e5 20. Nf3 Qe7 (20... Qxc6 21. Bxe5 Qe8 (21... Ne4 22. Rd8+) 22. Bxg7 Ne4 23. Qb4 Kxg7 24. Rd3 $16) 21. Rd5 $16) 19. Nb3 Qxc6 ({Quite nice variations (leading to White's advantage) can be seen after} 19... Nxb3 20. axb3 Rac8 21. Rd7 $1 Qxd7 (21... Qxc6 22. Qxc6 Rxc6 23. c4 a5 24. Ra7 $16 { d1-d7}) 22. cxd7 Rxc4 23. bxc4 g5 (23... f6 24. Ra1 a5 25. c5 $18) 24. Bxg5 f6 25. Bh4 Rd8 26. Rd1 Kf7 27. f4 $1 exf4 (27... e4 28. g4 $18) (27... Ke6 28. fxe5 Kxe5 29. Bg3+ Ke6 30. Bb8 a5 31. Rd6+ Ke7 32. Rxb6 $18) 28. exf4 Ke7 29. c5 $1 Rxd7 (29... bxc5 30. Bf2 Rxd7 31. Bxc5+ Ke8 32. Rxd7 Kxd7 33. Bxa7 $18) 30. Rxd7+ Kxd7 31. cxb6 axb6 32. f5 $18) 20. Nxc5 bxc5 $6 ({I think that Black had to accept a slightly worst endgame with} 20... Qxc5 $5 21. Qxc5 bxc5 22. Rd7 Rfb8 23. Rhd1 e4 24. c4 $14 {due to the white rook's presence on the 7th rank.}) 21. Rd5 Rab8 ({Interesting is the immediate} 21... g5 $5 22. Bg3 $1 (22. Bxg5 $2 Qg6 23. Be7 Rfb8 24. Rhd1 Qxg2 25. Rd8+ Rxd8 26. Rxd8+ Rxd8 27. Bxd8 $11) 22... Rad8 23. Rhd1 Rxd5 24. Rxd5 Rb8 25. e4 Rb2+ (25... Qe6 $2 26. Rxc5 (26. Qxc5 $2 Qa6+ (26... Rb2+ 27. Ke3 $16) 27. Ke3 Qf1 28. Bxe5 Bxe5 29. Rxe5 Qc1+ 30. Kd3 Qd1+ $11) 26... Rb2+ 27. Kd3 $16 (27. Kd1 $2 Rb1+ 28. Kc2 Qb6 29. Rc7 Rb2+ $11)) 26. Kd3 $1 $16 {It is quite funny that the white king feels no danger. The light-square control by the white side, guarantees his safety.} (26. Rd2 $2 Qb6 27. Qd5 Rxd2+ (27... Qa6+ 28. Ke3) 28. Qxd2 g4 29. c4 h5 $11)) 22. Rhd1 $16 {[White enjoys a significant advantage: better bishop, control of the light-squares and weak black pawns on c5 and e5.]} g5 23. Bg3 h5 24. h4 (24. Kf1 Rfe8 25. h4 $16) 24... gxh4 25. Bxe5 {[Yes, the black king is weaker!]} Rb2+ (25... Bxe5 26. Rxe5 Qxg2 27. Qxh4 $16) 26. R1d2 (26. Kf1 Bxe5 27. Rxe5 Qf6 28. f4 $16) 26... Rxd2+ 27. Kxd2 Bxe5 28. Rxe5 Rd8+ (28... Qxg2 29. Qxh4 $16) 29. Ke2 Qg6 $6 ({Black had to try} 29... Qxg2 30. Qxh4 Qg4+ 31. Qxg4+ hxg4 32. Rxc5 {although she has no chance in the resulting rook ending.}) 30. Qxh4 $18 Qc2+ 31. Kf3 Qd1+ 32. Kg3 Rd6 33. Rxh5 Rg6+ 34. Kh2 Qd6+ 35. g3 Qd2 36. Kg2 Qd6 37. Rh8+ Kg7 38. Rd8 Qc6+ 39. e4 Rh6 40. Qe7 Rg6 41. Qf8+ 1-0


