1. d4 Nf6 2. Nf3 g6 3. g3 Bg7 4. Bg2 O-O 5. O-O d6 6. a4 Na6 7. Nc3 c5 8. h3 Bd7 ({As usual, Black can try some alternatives: a)} 8... cxd4 9. Nxd4 Nc5 10. Be3 Bd7 11. a5 Qc8 12. Kh2 d5 13. Nf3 e6 14. Bd4 Rd8 15. Ne5 $14 {Salov,V-Gelfand,B/Linares 1993}) ({b)} 8... d5 9. Be3 Ne4 10. Nb5 c4 11. Nd2 f5 12. Nxe4 fxe4 (12... dxe4 $2 13. Qd2 Be6 14. Rad1 Bd5 15. Bf4 $16 {Talon,A-Filipek,J/Belgium 2003}) 13. Qd2 Bd7 14. f3 exf3 15. exf3 Qb6 16. Nc3 e6 17. f4 $14) ({c)} 8... Nd7 9. e4 cxd4 10. Nxd4 Ne5 11. Nd5 Bd7 12. b3 e6 13. Ne3 Qb6 14. Bb2 $14 {Nemet,I-Popovic,D/Pula 2006}) 9. e4 cxd4 10. Nxd4 Nc5 11. Be3 ({Interesting is} 11. a5 Qc8 12. Kh2 Rd8 13. Nd5 Re8 14. Re1 Ne6 15. Ne2 $14 {Rukavina,J-Minic,D/Zagreb 1977}) 11... a6 ({Black cannot really do without this move:} 11... Rc8 12. Re1 b6 13. Ra3 Qc7 $2 14. Bg5 a6 (14... Ne6 15. Bxf6 Bxf6 16. Nd5) 15. Bxf6 exf6 16. b4 Ne6 17. Nd5 Qd8 18. c3 $16 Re8 19. a5 b5 20. Nb6 Rc7 21. h4 Nxd4 22. cxd4 Bc6 {½-½ Zakharevich,I-Sakaev,K/St Petersburg 1996}) 12. a5 Rc8 13. Re1 $14 e5 $6 (13... Qc7 14. Bg5 e6 15. Ra3 $14) 14. Nb3 $6 (14. Nde2 $1 Bc6 15. f3 Ne6 16. Nd5 $16) 14... Nxb3 15. cxb3 Bc6 16. b4 Qe7 17. Re2 $6 (17. Qd3 Qe6 18. Red1 $14) 17... Qe6 18. b3 Ne8 19. g4 Nc7 20. Rd2 Qe7 $5 21. Rxd6 Ne6 $44 22. Bc5 Qh4 23. Rxe6 $6 (23. Nd5 Rfe8 24. Qf3 Nd4 25. Nf6+ Bxf6 26. Qxf6 Qxf6 27. Rxf6 Nxb3 $11) 23... fxe6 24. Bxf8 Bxf8 25. b5 $5 axb5 26. Qe2 Bc5 $6 (26... b4 $1 27. Na4 Bxa4 28. bxa4 Bc5 29. a6 bxa6 30. Qxa6 Qxf2+ 31. Kh1 Re8 32. a5 $15) 27. Nxb5 $1 Bxb5 28. Qxb5 Bxf2+ 29. Kh1 {And now a comedy of errors begins:} Rc3 $2 (29... Bd4 30. Rf1 Qe7 $11) 30. Qe8+ $2 $11 (30. Qxe5 $18) 30... Kg7 31. Qd7+ Kf8 $2 (31... Kh8 32. Qe8+ $11) 32. Qd6+ Kf7 33. Qxe5 Be1 $2 (33... Qf6 34. Qxf6+ Kxf6 35. Rf1 Rc2 36. e5+ Kxe5 37. Bxb7 $16) 34. g5 $2 (34. Qf4+ Kg8 35. Qb8+ Kg7 36. Qxb7+ Kg8 37. Qb8+ Kf7 38. Qf4+ Kg8 39. a6 $18) 34... Rxh3+ 35. Bxh3 Qxh3+ 36. Qh2 Qf1+ 37. Qg1 1/2-1/2


