1. d4 d5 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 Nf6 4. Nc3 Be7 5. Bg5 O-O 6. e3 h6 7. Bh4 b6 8. Bd3 Bb7 9. O-O Nbd7 10. cxd5 $5 Nxd5 (10... exd5 11. Qe2 Ne4 12. Bxe7 Qxe7 13. Rfd1 {transposes.}) 11. Bg3 $1 N7f6 (11... Nxc3 12. bxc3 c5 13. e4 $14 {.}) 12. Nxd5 Bxd5 $6 (12... exd5 13. Rc1 $14 {.}) 13. Qe2 Ne4 (13... c5 14. Rfd1 $1 cxd4 (14... Bxf3 15. Qxf3 cxd4 16. Ba6 $1) 15. Nxd4 $14 {.}) 14. Be5 $1 Bd6 (14... f6 15. Qc2 $1 {.}) 15. Rfd1 Qe7 16. Rac1 {Black has failed to achieve the equalizing ...c5 under favourable conditions. His position is now inferior, and becomes even worse after his next move.} f5 $6 17. Bc4 $1 Nf6 18. Bxd5 Nxd5 (18... exd5 19. Qd3 $1 Ne4 20. Rc6 $1 $16 {.}) 19. a3 Nf6 20. Rc6 $1 Nd7 21. Bxd6 cxd6 22. Rdc1 a6 {White somewhat "improved" Black's pawn structure but has fulfilled the important aim of occupying the c-file. The exploitation of this advantage is not difficult but requires concentration and thought.} 23. Qc4 $1 {Threatening 24.b4 and thus forcing Black to weaken the e5-square.} d5 24. Qd3 Ra7 25. g3 Kh7 26. Kg2 Rf6 27. Qc3 b5 28. Rc7 $1 $16 {The exchange of the "good" c7-rook for the "bad" a7-rook will allow White quicker access to Black's weak queenside pawns.} Rxc7 29. Qxc7 Rf7 30. Qb7 $1 b4 31. Qxa6 bxa3 32. bxa3 e5 33. Rc7 $1 $18 exd4 34. Rxd7 $1 Qxd7 35. Ne5 Qe7 36. Qg6+ ({Black resigned due to} 36. Qg6+ Kg8 37. Qxf7+ Qxf7 38. Nxf7 Kxf7 (38... d3 39. Kf1 $18) (38... dxe3 39. Ne5 $1) 39. exd4 $18) 1-0


