1. d4 Nf6 2. Nf3 d5 3. c4 e6 4. Nc3 Be7 5. Bg5 O-O 6. e3 Nbd7 7. Bd3 dxc4 8. Bxc4 c5 9. O-O h6 10. Bh4 cxd4 11. exd4 Nb6 12. Bb3 {I think that inserting ...h6 move is in White's favour as Black has weakened his kingside without any particular reason. Also White has added the g3 possibility to his future ideas.} Nbd5 $6 ({Alternatives are: a)} 12... Bd7 13. Ne5 (13. Qd3 Nbd5 (13... Bc6 14. Bc2 Nbd7 15. Rad1 Re8 16. Rfe1 Nf8 17. Ne5 Qa5 (17... N6d7 18. Nxc6 (18. Bxe7 Rxe7 19. Ng4 Ng6 20. Qg3 Ndf8 21. Ne5 Nxe5 22. dxe5 Rd7 23. Rxd7 {½-½ Winants,L-Gaprindashvili,N/Brussels 1987}) 18... bxc6 19. Bg3 $16) 18. a3 $1 Rac8 19. Nxc6 bxc6 20. Bg3 $16) 14. Ne5 Bc6 15. Bxf6 Bxf6 16. Bc2 Re8 17. Qh7+ (17. Rad1 Kf8 18. Nxc6 bxc6 19. Ba4 Rb8 $13 {Novikov,I-Tal,M/Soviet Union 1985}) 17... Kf8 18. Ne4 $14) 13... Nfd5 14. Bxe7 Qxe7 15. Re1 Nxc3 16. bxc3 Qa3 17. Re3 $16 {Stephan,O-Ganske,M/Kettig 1994.}) ({b)} 12... Nfd5 13. Bg3 $1 Nxc3 14. bxc3 Bd7 15. Ne5 Rc8 16. c4 $16 {Haritakis,T-Mitsakis,K/Ikaria 1993.}) ({c)} 12... Nh5 13. Bxe7 Qxe7 14. Ne5 Nf6 15. Qf3 Rd8 16. Rad1 Nbd5 17. Rfe1 $16 {Nikoladze,S-Matnadze,A/Tbilisi 2002.}) ({d)} 12... Re8 13. Re1 Bd7 14. Ne5 Rc8 15. Qd3 (15. Qf3 $5 Bc6 16. Qh3 $14 {Etemadi,S-Watai,M/Kuala Lumpur 1993}) 15... Nfd5 16. Bg3 $14 {. I feel that Black should choose the last option.}) 13. Ne5 Nxc3 14. bxc3 Nd7 (14... Ne4 15. Bxe7 Qxe7 16. Qd3 Nf6 17. f4 Bd7 18. Rae1 Qd6 19. Rf3 $16 {.}) 15. Bg3 $6 (15. Bxe7 {seems to give White the advantage:} Qxe7 16. f4 Nxe5 (16... b6 17. Qd3 Bb7 18. Rae1 Nxe5 19. Rxe5 (19. fxe5 Qg5 20. Rf2 Rfc8 21. Bc2 g6 22. Re3 $16 {Gonzalez Garcia,J-Amura,C/Mexico 1997}) 19... g6 20. Qh3 $16) 17. fxe5 Bd7 18. Qd3 Rac8 19. Bc2 g6 20. Rf6 $16 {.}) 15... Nxe5 16. Bxe5 Bd7 17. Qg4 Bf6 18. f4 Bc6 (18... Bxe5 19. fxe5 Qg5 20. Qxg5 hxg5 21. Rf3 Rac8 $14 {.}) 19. Rae1 Bxe5 20. Rxe5 $14 Bd5 21. Bxd5 $6 (21. f5 exf5 22. Qxf5 Bxb3 23. axb3 $14 {.}) 21... exd5 22. f5 (22. Qf3 Qa5 23. Rxd5 Qxa2 24. Rd7 Rac8 25. Rxb7 Qa3 $11 {.}) 22... f6 23. Re6 Qa5 $1 24. Rf3 Qxa2 25. h3 $1 $44 Qa4 26. Re7 (26. Rg3 Qd7 (26... Rf7 $2 27. Rxf6) 27. Rd6 Qf7 28. Rxd5 a5 $13 {.}) 26... Rf7 27. Rxf7 Kxf7 28. Rg3 Rg8 29. Qg6+ Kf8 30. Re3 Qd7 31. Re6 a5 32. Qg3 Kf7 $1 33. Qg6+ Kf8 34. Qg3 Kf7 35. Qg6+ 1/2-1/2


