1. d4 d6 2. Nf3 Nf6 3. g3 g6 4. Bg2 Bg7 5. O-O O-O 6. a4 a5 7. Nc3 Na6 8. e4 Nd7 $6 ({I do not really believe this idea. Black should instead chose one of the following options: a)} 8... c6 9. h3 Qc7 (9... Nb4 10. Be3 (10. Bf4 Nh5 11. Bg5 f6 12. Be3 e5 13. Qe2 Qe7 14. Rad1 Be6 15. d5 Bf7 16. Qd2 $14 {Naumann,F-Sawatzki,F/Germany 1997}) 10... Qc7 11. Qd2 e5 12. Rfd1 $14 {½-½ Romanishin,O-Damljanovic,B/Calvia 2006}) 10. Be3 Bd7 11. e5 Ne8 12. Bf4 $14 {Markov,J-Ori,M/Budapest 1992}) ({b)} 8... Bg4 9. Bg5 h6 10. Be3 c6 11. Qc1 Bxf3 12. Bxf3 Kh7 13. Kg2 e5 14. dxe5 dxe5 15. Be2 $14 {Doroshkievich,V-Ryskin,A/Sochi 1993}) ({c)} 8... Nb4 9. h3 e5 10. d5 c6 11. Ne1 cxd5 12. exd5 Bf5 13. Nb5 Be4 14. Bg5 Bxg2 15. Nxg2 Qd7 16. Bxf6 Bxf6 17. c3 Na6 18. Qg4 $14 {Mastrovasilis,A-Kurnosov,I/Warsaw 2005}) 9. Be3 e5 10. Qd2 c6 11. Bh6 $1 {After the exchange of the dark-squared bishops, Black will have a hard time finding counterplay} Qc7 12. Rad1 Nb4 13. Bxg7 Kxg7 14. Ne2 $14 Nf6 15. Nh4 $1 Be6 16. b3 Rad8 17. f4 d5 $2 (17... exd4 18. Nxd4 Na6 19. Qc3 $14) 18. exd5 Bxd5 19. fxe5 Ne4 20. Qf4 g5 21. Nf5+ Kg6 22. Qc1 c5 23. c4 Bc6 24. Nf4+ $1 gxf4 (24... Kxf5 25. Bh3+ g4 26. Bxg4+ Kxg4 27. h3+ Kf5 28. g4+ Kg5 29. Ne6+ Kh4 30. Qh6+ Kg3 31. Qf4+ Kh4 32. Rf3 fxe6 33. Qh6#) 25. Qxf4 Ng5 26. Nh4+ Kh6 27. Qf6+ Kh5 28. Nf5 1-0


