1. c4 {Grivas,E Grivas,E Nigel Davies} Nf6 2. Nc3 d5 3. cxd5 Nxd5 4. Nf3 g6 5. Qa4+ $5 {* Nigel Davies: '!?'} c6 $5 {Nigel Davies: '!?'} ({a)} 5... Bd7 6. Qh4 (6. Qb3 Nb6 7. d4 Be6 8. Qc2 Bg7 9. e4 Bg4 10. Ne5 Bxe5 11. dxe5 Nc6 12. Bb5 Bd7 13. Bxc6 Bxc6 14. Be3 $14 {Gelfand,B-Shirov,A/Dagomys 2008}) 6... Nxc3 7. dxc3 e5 8. Bg5 Be7 9. e4 Nc6 10. Bc4 h6 11. Bxe7 Qxe7 12. Qg3 $14 {Kramnik,V-Ivanchuk,V/Las Palmas 1996.}) ({b)} 5... Nc6 6. Ne5 Ndb4 (6... Nb6 $2 7. Nxc6 Nxa4 8. Nxd8 Nxc3 9. Nxf7 $16 {Krasenkow,M-Azmaiparashvili,Z/Groningen 1997}) (6... Nxc3 7. bxc3 Bd7 8. Nxd7 Qxd7 9. Rb1 $14 {Damljanovic,B-Prada Rubin,F/La Coruna 1998}) 7. a3 Nc2+ (7... Bg7 8. axb4 Bxe5 9. b5 Nb8 10. e3 O-O 11. d4 Bg7 12. Be2 c6 13. O-O $14 {Ionov,S-Gubanov,A/St.Petersburg 1997}) 8. Qxc2 Nxe5 9. d4 $1 Nd7 (9... Qxd4 $2 10. Nb5 $18) 10. Bf4 c6 11. Rd1 $14 {Kortcnoi,V-Berkes,F/Paks 2007.}) 6. Qd4 $1 (6. Nxd5 {(Nigel Davies) seems to be a simpler and more economical choice, my preference being for White because of his central pawn majority.}) 6... f6 (6... Nf6 $6 {Ü 12/23} 7. Qxd8+ Kxd8 8. e4 (8. d4 b6 (8... Bf5 9. Ng5 Ke8 10. e4 Bd7 11. Bc4 e6 12. e5 Nd5 13. Nge4 h6 14. Bd2 Be7 15. O-O $16 {Pachman,L-Beggi,P/Reggio Emilia 1975}) 9. e4 Nfd7 10. Bc4 Ke8 11. Bf4 Ba6 12. Bb3 e6 13. O-O-O $16 {Alekhine,A-Rellstab,L/Kemeri 1937}) 8... Nbd7 9. d4 Bg7 10. Bc4 e6 11. O-O b5 12. Bd3 a5 13. Bf4 Ba6 14. Rfe1 $16 {Volzhin,A-Murawski,G/Wisla 1998.}) (6... Rg8 {Ü 32/18}) 7. e4 {(D) } e5 $1 ({a)} 7... Nb6 $2 8. Qxd8+ Kxd8 9. d4 Bg4 10. Be3 N8d7 11. O-O-O $16 {Milov,V-Zollbrecht,J/Biel 1998.}) ({b)} 7... Nc7 $2 8. Qxd8+ Kxd8 9. d4 Bg4 10. Be3 Nd7 11. Be2 Ke8 12. O-O $16 {Petursson,M-Fries Nielsen,J/Graz 1978.}) ({c)} 7... Nxc3 $2 8. Qxc3 $1 e5 {Nigel Davies: 'is difficult for Black after'} (8... Bg4 $6 9. d4 Bxf3 10. gxf3 a5 11. Be3 e5 12. O-O-O $18 {Savchenko,S-Roeber,B/Gelsenkirchen 1999}) 9. Bc4 {Nigel Davies: 'because he'll have trouble getting his king to safety and meanwhile White can open it up with d2-d4.'} Bg7 10. O-O Qe7 11. d4 Nd7 12. Be3 exd4 13. Nxd4 Ne5 14. Bb3 $16 f5 $6 15. exf5 Bxf5 16. Nxf5 gxf5 17. Bc5 Qh4 18. f4 Ng4 19. Rfe1+ Be5 20. Rxe5+ {1-0 Delchev,A-Kukovec,B/Nova Gorica 2000.}) 8. Nxe5 {Nigel Davies: '!?'} (8. Qd3 $6 Nb4 (8... Nxc3 9. Qxd8+ Kxd8 10. dxc3 Be6 11. Be3 Nd7 $11 {Degenhardt,H-Konopka,M/Griesheim 2002}) 9. Qb1 Be6 $1 10. a3 N4a6 11. b4 c5 $1 12. b5 Nc7 $11 {Jaworski,M-Navara,D/Czech Rep. 1999.}) 8... Nxc3 $1 {Nigel Davies: 'The only good reply.'} ({a) a) Nigel Davies: 'Both'} 8... Qe7 9. Nxd5 cxd5 (9... fxe5 10. Nxe7 exd4 11. Nxc8 Nd7 12. Nxa7 Rxa7 13. a3 Nc5 14. d3 $16) 10. Bb5+ Nd7 11. Nxd7 Bxd7 12. Qxd5 $16 {Ostrowski,L-Duesterwald,M/Gausdal 2003.}) ({b) b) Nigel Davies: 'and'} 8... Nb4 9. Qxd8+ Kxd8 10. Nf7+ Ke8 11. Nxh8 Nc2+ 12. Kd1 Nxa1 13. b3 Be6 (13... Bg7 14. Nxg6 hxg6 15. Bb2 Nxb3 16. axb3 $16 {Nigel Davies: 'are good for White.'}) 14. Bc4 Bxc4 15. bxc4 Bg7 16. Nxg6 hxg6 17. Bb2 Nd7 18. Bxa1 Ne5 19. c5 Nd3 20. Ke2 Nxc5 21. d4 $16 {.}) ({c)} 8... fxe5 9. Qxe5+ Qe7 10. Qxh8 Nxc3 11. dxc3 Qxe4+ 12. Be3 Bf5 13. Be2 $18 {.}) 9. Qxc3 (9. Qxd8+ $2 Kxd8 10. Nf7+ Ke8 11. Nxh8 Nxe4 12. Bc4 Nd6 13. Bg8 (13. Bb3 $2 Bg7 $17) 13... Bg7 14. Bxh7 Bxh8 15. Bxg6+ Kf8 16. d3 Bf5 17. Bh6+ Bg7 18. Bxg7+ Kxg7 19. Bxf5 {½-½ Marosi,G-Frank,J/Hungary 2002.}) 9... Qe7 10. Nf3 $1 (10. Nc4 Qxe4+ 11. Kd1 $5 Kf7 $1 12. b3 Be6 13. Bb2 Nd7 14. Bd3 Qd5 $13 {Mohr,G-Kozul,Z/Maribor 1993.}) 10... Qxe4+ (10... Bg7 $2 11. d3 O-O 12. Be2 Be6 13. O-O Nd7 14. Qc2 Rae8 15. Be3 c5 16. Rac1 $16 {Apro,A-Elo,I/Hungary 1994.}) 11. Be2 {(D) } ({Rybka's novelty is} 11. Kd1 $5 {(Nigel Davies) but is it really that great? I think Black can defend himself with} Nd7 12. Bc4 Kd8 $1 {when} 13. Re1 Qg4 14. Be6 $6 (14. g3 Kc7 {is fine for Black}) 14... Qxg2 15. d4 Bd6 {is unconvincing.}) 11... Bg7 $2 ({a) a) Nigel Davies: 'Black should play'} 11... Nd7 $1 {Nigel Davies: 'when' Nigel Davies: '!' Nigel Davies: 'when'} 12. O-O Bb4 13. Qe3 (13. d3 $5 Qe7 14. Qc2 Nb6 (14... O-O 15