1. d4 Nf6 2. Nf3 g6 3. g3 Bg7 4. Bg2 O-O 5. O-O d6 6. a4 Nbd7 7. a5 {Although other moves have been tried by White instead of the text-move, I believe that this should be his main try.} a6 ({As it happens nearly always, Black has at his disposal two other main options: a)} 7... c6 8. Nc3 (8. c4 e5 9. Nc3 Re8 10. e4 exd4 11. Nxd4 Nc5 12. f3 Nfd7 13. Be3 Ne5 14. Qe2 Ne6 15. Nb3 $11 {Romanishin,O-Pervakov,S/Alushta 2005}) 8... Qc7 9. e4 e5 10. h3 Re8 11. Re1 Nf8 12. Be3 $14 {Romanishin,O-Schmidt,G/Dresden 1998}) ({b)} 7... c5 8. Nc3 Rb8 9. Nb5 a6 10. Na7 cxd4 11. Nxd4 Nc5 12. Nxc8 Qxc8 13. c3 {and White should somewhat better due to his bishop-pair, as in Romanishin,O-Socko,B/Koszalin 1997}) 8. Nc3 ({I think that} 8. d5 e5 9. dxe6 fxe6 10. c4 Rb8 11. Nc3 Qe8 {is acceptable for Black, as in Bauer,C-Toulzac,P/Cap d'Agde 1998}) 8... c5 ({a)} 8... Qe8 $6 9. e4 e5 10. h3 h6 11. Re1 Kh7 12. Be3 Qe7 13. Qe2 Ne8 14. Rad1 c6 15. dxe5 dxe5 16. Nd2 $16 {Romanishin,O-Ljubicic,F/Zadar 1995}) ({b)} 8... e5 9. e4 exd4 10. Nxd4 Re8 11. Re1 Ne5 12. h3 $14 c5 $6 13. Nf3 Ned7 14. Nd2 $16 {Lerner,K-Mamedov,R/Moscow 2005}) 9. d5 ({The text-move looks more ambitious than} 9. e4 Qc7 (9... cxd4 10. Nxd4 Nc5 11. h3 Bd7 12. b4 Ne6 13. Be3 Rc8 14. Qd3 Qc7 15. Nde2 Nd8 16. Bb6 Qb8 17. Rab1 $14 {Sosonko,G-Browne,W/Wijk aan Zee 1974}) 10. h3 cxd4 11. Nxd4 Ne5 12. Qe2 Nc4 13. Nb3 Bd7 14. Rd1 Rac8 15. Kh2 Rfd8 $11 {Romanishin,O-Gojak,I/Zadar 1995}) 9... b5 10. axb6 Nxb6 11. e4 Bd7 (11... Qc7 12. h3 Bb7 13. Re1 Rad8 14. Na4 Nbd7 15. Bd2 e6 16. c4 exd5 17. cxd5 Rfe8 18. Qc2 $16 {Romanishin,O-Todorcevic,M/Zaragoza 1996}) 12. h3 $14 Ne8 13. Re1 Nc7 14. e5 $1 Nb5 15. Ne4 Qc8 16. e6 $2 (16. exd6 exd6 17. Kh2 $14 {was the correct continuation. White felt too optimistic!}) 16... fxe6 17. dxe6 Bxe6 18. Neg5 Bd5 19. Rxe7 Qf5 $6 (19... h6 $1 20. Nh4 Bxg2 21. Ne6 Rf7 (21... Bf6 22. Qd3) 22. Rxf7 Kxf7 23. Nxg7 Be4 (23... Bc6 $2 24. Qd3 $18) 24. f3 Qxh3 25. fxe4 Qxg3+ 26. Ng2 Kxg7 27. Bf4 Qh3 28. Bxd6 c4 $13) 20. Re2 h6 $4 ({The right move at the wrong time!} 20... Qd7 21. c3 Bxc3 $5 22. bxc3 Nxc3 23. Qe1 Nxe2+ 24. Qxe2 Rae8 25. Qc2 $13 {was calling for}) 21. Nh4 $1 {Black loses at least a piece} 1-0


