1. c4 e6 2. Nc3 d5 3. d4 Nf6 4. Bg5 Be7 5. e3 O-O 6. Nf3 Nbd7 7. Bd3 dxc4 8. Bxc4 c5 (8... c6 9. a4 Nd5 10. Bxe7 Qxe7 11. O-O Rd8 12. a5 $1 $14 {Grivas,E-Haritakis,T/Corfu 1988.}) (8... b6 {may be compared with the game Grivas,E-Gabriel,Ch/Budapest 1994.}) 9. O-O Nb6 (9... a6 {would transpose to the game Grivas,E- Georgiou,An/Thessaloniki 1988.}) 10. Bb3 cxd4 11. exd4 Bd7 ({Black can also play} 11... Nfd5 12. Bxe7 Qxe7 13. Re1 Rd8 14. Rc1 Nxc3 (14... Nf6 15. Qe2 Qb4 16. Ne4 Nbd5 17. Nc5 $14 {Kortschnoj,V-Zaitsev,I /Yerevan Ch-URS 1962}) 15. Rxc3 Bd7 16. d5 Qd6 17. dxe6 Bxe6 18. Qxd6 Rxd6 19. Bxe6 Rxe6 20. Rxe6 fxe6 21. Rc7 Rd8 22. Kf1 Rd7 23. Rxd7 Nxd7 $14 {Timman,J-Ree,H/Amsterdam 1984 or}) (11... Nbd5 12. Ne5 (12. Qe2 b6 13. Ne5 Bb7 14. Rfe1 Nxc3 15. bxc3 Ne4 16. Bxe7 Qxe7 17. Qd3 $14 {Casafus,R-Mendez,G/Buenos Aires 1993}) 12... Nxc3 (12... Nd7 $6 13. Bxe7 Nxe7 14. Qe2 $16 {Botvinnik,M-Batuyev,A/Leningrad 1930}) (12... Qd6 13. Qf3 Nxc3 14. bxc3 Ne8 15. Bf4 $16 {Kovalenko,I-Marchenko,A/Dnipropetrovsk 2005}) 13. bxc3 Nd7 14. Bf4 (14. Bxe7 $5 Qxe7 15. f4 Nxe5 16. fxe5 $14) 14... Nxe5 15. Bxe5 Bd6 16. Re1 $1 (16. Qe2 Bxe5 17. Qxe5 Bd7 $11 {Kapnisis,S-Bunis,V/Ermioni 2005}) 16... Bxe5 17. Rxe5 Bd7 18. Qd3 Bc6 19. Rae1 $14 {.}) 12. Ne5 ({Alternatives are: a)} 12. Qd3 Nbd5 $6 (12... Bc6 13. Bc2 g6 14. Bh6 Re8 15. Ne5 Nbd5 16. Bb3 Nb4 17. Qh3 Bd5 18. Nxd5 Nfxd5 19. Ba4 $16 {Sanguineti,R-Cuasnicu,O/Zarate 1973}) 13. Ne5 Bc6 14. Rad1 (14. Nxc6 bxc6 15. Rfd1 Rb8 {½-½ Breder,D-Fridman,R/Germany 2005}) 14... Nb4 (14... Nxc3 15. bxc3 Be4 16. Qe2 Bf5 17. Rfe1 $16 {Yurkov,V-Gaprindashvili,N/Parnu 1973}) (14... Rc8 15. Qh3 (15. f3 $5 {Stempin,P-Panczyk,K/Polanica Zdroj 1982}) 15... Nxc3 16. bxc3 $14 {Tajvidi,A-Bagheri,A/Iran 1997}) 15. Qh3 $14 Bd5 16. Nxd5 Nbxd5 17. f4 Rc8 18. f5 exf5 19. Rxf5 Qd6 20. Nxf7 Rxf7 21. Bxf6 Bxf6 22. Rxd5 Qc6 23. Rd6 Qe8 24. Rd7 {1-0 Botvinnik,M-Vidmar,M/Nottingham 1936.}) ({b)} 12. Qe2 Bc6 13. Rfd1 (13. Rad1 Nfd5 14. Bxe7 Qxe7 15. Ne5 Rfd8 16. Rfe1 Rac8 17. Ne4 $13 {Kindl,P-Arbakov,V/Groningen 1994}) 13... Bd5 14. Nxd5 Nfxd5 15. Bd2 $14 {Spraggett,K-Saidy,A/New York 1986.}) 12... Rc8 ({Black's other options are: a)} 12... Bc6 13. Nxc6 bxc6 14. Rc1 $14 {.}) ({b)} 12... Be8 13. Re1 Nfd5 14. Bd2 Nb4 15. Qg4 Nc6 16. Bh6 Bf6 17. Rad1 $16 {Lukacs,P-Almasi,I/Budapest 1997.}) ({c)} 12... Nfd5 13. Bxe7 Nxe7 14. Qf3 (14. Qg4 $5 $14) 14... Nc6 15. Rfd1 Nxe5 16. dxe5 Qc7 17. Qf4 $14 {Hoi,C-Holst,A/Taastrup 1998.}) 13. Qd3 $5 Bc6 ({Of course, as always, Black can choose also among: a)} 13... Nfd5 14. Bd2 Bc6 15. Rad1 Bf6 16. Nxc6 Rxc6 17. Ne4 $14 {Langeweg,K-Ree,H/Leeuwarden 1980.}) ({b)} 13... Nbd5 14. Rfe1 Bc6 15. Qh3 (15. Nxc6 bxc6 $1 (15... Rxc6 $6 16. Nxd5 exd5 $16 {Kitts,G-Schoonmaker,J/Lansing 1988}) 16. Rad1 Qc7 17. Nxd5 cxd5 18. Rc1 Qb7 19. f3 Rxc1 20. Rxc1 Rc8 $11 {Ressler,V-Kopera,M/Slovakia 2001}) 15... a6 16. Rad1 b5 17. Bc2 $14 Qd6 $2 18. Nxc6 Rxc6 19. Bxf6 Nxf6 20. Ne4 {1-0 Bronstein,D-Berger,B/Amsterdam 1964.}) 14. Bc2 $1 (14. Nxc6 Rxc6 15. Rfd1 (15. Rfe1 a6 16. Rad1 Rd6 17. Bc2 g6 $13 {Funk,P-Domnick,A/Germany 1994}) 15... Nfd5 16. Bxe7 Nxe7 17. Bc2 Ng6 $11 {Lasker,E-Steinitz,W/USA/CAN 1894.}) 14... g6 15. Bh6 Re8 16. Rfe1 ({White has activated all his pieces, also succeeding in weakening the black king's cover in the process. Even more important is the fact that Black has failed to exchange any pieces. As a result, his position is uncomfortable and requires increased attention.} 16. Rad1 a6 17. Rfe1 Nbd5 18. Qh3 Bf8 19. Bb3 $14 {Liersch,A-Eichhorn,E/Buesum 1967 looks also good.}) 16... Nbd5 17. Bb3 $1 $14 {The bishop's mission on the b1-h7 diagonal has been completed, so it switches to the very promising a2-g8 one. At the same time White prevents piece exchanges with 17...xc3? 18.xf7!!.} Bf8 ({Maybe Black should try} 17... Qa5 $5 $14 {, intending ...xc3 and ...a4, when White retains an edge but Black succeeds in exchanging some pieces, thus relieving his position.}) 18. Bg5 $1 Qa5 $6 (18... Bg7 19. Nxc6 bxc6 20. Ne4 $14 {.}) 19. Qf3 $1 Bg7 $6 (19... Be7 20. Nxd5 Bxd5 21. Qf4 $1 Qd8 22. Bxd5 exd5 23. Re2 $16 {.}) 20. Ne4 $1 (20. Bxd5 $2 {is a mistake, as after} Bxd5 21. Nxd5 Qxd5 {Black can survive.}) ({Now after} 20. Ne4 {there is no satisfactory defence, as Black loses quickly after} Nxe4 (20... Qd8 21. Nxc6 Rxc6 22. Bxd5 exd5 23. Nxf6+ Bxf6 24. Rxe8+ Qxe8 25. Bxf6 $18) 21. Qxf7+ Kh8 22. Rxe4 {with an extra pawn and the threat 23.xg6+ hxg6 24.h4+.}) 1-0


