 Huzman,Alexander: '(Huebner,Robert) ( f6-d7)'} 22. Bg5 $5 $14) (21... f5 {Huzman,Alexander} 22. Rfe3 $14) 22. Be3 f5 23. Bd4 fxe4 ({Grivas,Efstratios: 'Black could equalize with the simple (and more concrete)'} 23... Bxd4 $5 {Grivas,Efstratios: '!' Huzman,Alexander: 'Huebner,Robert'} 24. Qxd4+ Qg7 25. Qxg7+ {Grivas,Efstratios} Kxg7 26. Rfe3 fxe4 27. Nxe4 Re5 $11) 24. Rxf8 Rxf8 25. Rxe4 Kh7 26. Ne2 {[e6] Grivas,Efstratios: '!?' Huzman,Alexander: 'Huebner,Robert: '[×e6]''} ({Grivas,Efstratios: 'Going for the weak e6-square.'} 26. Re6 $2 {Huzman,Alexander: 'Huebner,Robert'} Qf7 27. Re1 {Grivas,Efstratios} Qf3+ 28. Kh2 Rf7 $11) 26... Re8 ({Grivas,Efstratios: 'Interesting is'} 26... Qf5 $5 {Huzman,Alexander: 'Huebner,Robert'} 27. Rf4 Qb1 28. Rxf8 Bxf8 29. Nf4 Qe4+ 30. Kh2 Bg7 31. Bxg7 Kxg7 32. Ne6+ Kh7 33. Nxc7 Ne7 $13 {Grivas,Efstratios: 'when Black can find good compensation for the lost pawn in his better placed pieces but not'}) (26... Nf6 $5 {Grivas,Efstratios: '?' Huzman,Alexander: 'Huebner,Robert'} 27. Re6 Nh5 $13 {( Bd4, Ng7) Huzman,Alexander: '( d4, g7)'} 28. Qd3 (28. Qe3 {Grivas,Efstratios} Rf7 29. Qd3 $18) 28... Qf7) 27. Rxe8 Qxe8 28. Qd3 (28. Bxg7 {Huzman,Alexander: 'Huebner,Robert'} Qe4+ 29. Kh2 Kxg7 30. Nf4 Kh7 $11) 28... Qf7 29. Nf4 Bxd4 30. Qxd4 Qf6 $2 {Huzman,Alexander: 'Huebner,Robert: '?''} (30... Ne7 $13 {Huzman,Alexander: 'Huebner,Robert'} 31. Qa7 Nf5 { g5 Huzman,Alexander: ' g5'}) (30... Nf6 {Huzman,Alexander} 31. Ne6 $16) 31. Qxf6 Nxf6 32. Ne6 $18 {Huzman,Alexander: 'Huebner,Robert: '+-''} Ne8 ({Grivas,Efstratios: 'Black should not have exchanged queens, as he could have obtained a decent position with 30...e7 31.a7 f5! intending 32...g5, with unclear play. Now however, the knight ending that has arisen is won for White. The e6-knight is immensely superior to the e8-knight, while the black queenside pawns are potential and approachable targets. It must be noted that, instead of the passive 32...e8, the alternative'} 32... c6 {Huzman,Alexander: 'Huebner,Robert'} 33. dxc6 bxc6 34. b4 {Grivas,Efstratios: '!'} (34. Nd8 {Grivas,Efstratios: '?'} c5 35. Nb7 Ne8 36. Kf3 Kg7 37. Ke4 Nf6+ $11 {Grivas,Efstratios: '=!'}) 34... Kg8 35. Nc7 {Grivas,Efstratios: '!' Grivas,Efstratios: 'was not a help either.'}) 33. b4 {Grivas,Efstratios: '!' Huzman,Alexander: '!' '!' Huzman: '!'} ({Grivas,Efstratios: 'It is especially important to immobilize the weak a6-b7 pawn structure. The careless'} 33. Kf3 {Grivas,Efstratios: '?' Huzman,Alexander: 'Huebner,Robert'} a5 $13 {Grivas,Efstratios: '!' Grivas,Efstratios: 'would give Black serious hope for survival.'}) 33... b6 34. Kf3 Kg8 35. a4 Kf7 36. Nd8+ {Grivas,Efstratios: '!'} Ke7 (36... Kf6 {Huzman,Alexander: 'Huebner,Robert'} 37. Nc6 { a5 Huzman,Alexander: ' a5' Grivas,Efstratios: 'intending a5, would also win for White.'}) 37. Nc6+ Kd7 38. a5 {Grivas,Efstratios: '!' Huzman,Alexander: '!' '!' Huzman: '!'} ({Grivas,Efstratios: 'Clearly better than'} 38. Nb8+ {Huzman,Alexander: 'Huebner,Robert'} Kc8 39. Nxa6 $2 Kb7 40. b5 Nf6 $11 {Grivas,Efstratios: 'when Black has some survival chances.'}) 38... Nf6 $8 {Huzman,Alexander: 'Huebner,Robert: '''} ({Grivas,Efstratios: 'Or'} 38... Kc8 {Huzman,Alexander: 'Huebner,Robert'} 39. Ne7+) (38... bxa5 {Huzman,Alexander} 39. bxa5 $18 {[%cal Yc6b4]}) 39. b5 {Grivas,Efstratios: '!' Huzman,Alexander: '!' '!' Huzman: '!'} axb5 ({Grivas,Efstratios: 'Unfortunately,'} 39... bxa5 {Huzman,Alexander: 'Huebner,Robert'} 40. bxa6 Kc8 41. Nxa5 Kb8 42. Nc6+ Ka8 43. Ne7 {Grivas,Efstratios: '!'} g5 44. Nc6 {Grivas,Efstratios: 'also fails to help Black.'}) 40. a6 Kc8 41. Ne7+ Kb8 42. cxb5 {Huzman,Alexander: '+-' '+-' Huzman: '+-'} g5 43. Ke3 h5 (43... Ka8 {Huzman,Alexander: 'Huebner,Robert'} 44. Kd4 Kb8 45. Nf5 h5 (45... Ng8 46. Ne3 Nf6 47. Ng4 Ng8 48. Ke4) 46. Ne7 Ka8 {Huzman,Alexander: 'Huebner,Robert'} 47. Ke3 Kb8 48. h4 {Huzman,Alexander: 'Huebner,Robert'}) 44. Kd4 (44. h4) 44... h4 45. gxh4 gxh4 46. Ke3 1-0


