Black enjoys an undisputed superiority, with the bishop-pair in an open position. Tactics are in the air...} 19. Rd2 Rac8 20. Re1 Rfe8 21. Qb1 $2 (21. Kg1 $15) 21... Qh5 $2 (21... Rxe3 $1 22. Rxe3 Bxd4 23. Qd1 (23. Red3 Qf5) 23... Bxe3 $1 24. Rxd5 Bxd5 $19) 22. Qd1 Qh4 $1 23. Bf2 Qg5 24. Ne2 $6 (24. Rxe8+ Rxe8 25. Ne2 $15) 24... Rcd8 $1 25. Be3 Qh4 26. Rxd8 Rxd8 27. Qc1 Bxb2 28. Bg5 Qf2 $1 29. Qb1 Re8 30. Qd1 Bc3 31. Bd2 Bxd2 32. Qxd2 Bd5 {White resigned in view of 33.g1 xe2 34.xd5 e1 35.d8+ g7. A crystal-clear game, in which Black made exemplary use of his bishop-pair.} 0-1


