1. Nf3 Nf6 2. g3 g6 3. c4 Bg7 4. Bg2 O-O 5. O-O d6 6. d4 Nc6 7. Nc3 Bf5 8. Ne1 Qd7 9. e4 Bh3 {(D) } 10. f3 ({Alternatives are: a)} 10. d5 $6 Ne5 (10... Nd8 11. Be3 Bxg2 12. Kxg2 Ng4 13. Bd4 Bxd4 14. Qxd4 $11 {Skjoldan,B-Nielsen,J/Copenhagen 2005}) 11. Qe2 c6 12. f4 Bg4 13. Nf3 Nxf3+ 14. Bxf3 cxd5 15. cxd5 Bh3 16. Bg2 Rfc8 $11) ({b)} 10. Nf3 Bxg2 11. Kxg2 e5 12. d5 Ne7 (12... Na5 13. Qe2 b6 14. b4 Nb7 15. Rb1 Rfe8 16. h3 $14 {Ferris,S-Chu,L/Perth 2004}) 13. h3 h6 14. Be3 Nh5 15. Rc1 f5 $13 {Kaukal,T-Bekker Jensen,A/Tallinn 1997}) ({c)} 10. f4 {is covered in the next two games.}) 10... Bxg2 (10... a6 11. Be3 Bxg2 12. Kxg2 Rfb8 (12... Na5 13. Qd3 b5 14. cxb5 axb5 15. Nxb5 Rfb8 16. Nc3 Rxb2+ 17. Rf2 Rb7 18. Rb1 Rxb1 19. Qxb1 Ne8 20. Qd3 e6 {Stangl,M-Votava,J/Feugen 2006}) 13. Nd3 Na5 14. b3 b5 15. c5 Nb7 16. Qc2 dxc5 17. dxc5 Rd8 18. Rad1 Qe8 19. Rd2 c6 20. Rfd1 Nd7 21. a4 Nf8 22. b4 Ne6 23. Nf4 Rxd2+ 24. Rxd2 Nxf4+ 25. Bxf4 Rd8 26. axb5 axb5 27. Ne2 Rxd2 28. Qxd2 $11 {Froehlich,P-Slobodjan,R/Hamburg 1999}) 11. Kxg2 Na5 $5 (11... e5 12. d5 Nd4 13. Nc2 Nxc2 14. Qxc2 Nh5 15. Qe2 f5 $13 {Kanep,M-Bachmann,A/Turin OL 2006}) 12. b3 c5 13. Nc2 Ne8 (13... cxd4 14. Nxd4 Nc6 15. Be3 a6 16. Rc1 Rab8 17. Rf2 Rfc8 $11 {Lerner,K-Maiwald,J/Germany tt 1999}) 14. Be3 Nc6 15. Qd2 cxd4 16. Nxd4 Nc7 17. Rac1 Rfc8 {Black is OK, as in this Maroczy type position, the white king is too exposed.} 18. Nxc6 Qxc6 $6 (18... bxc6 {is not that bad.}) 19. Rc2 (19. Nd5 Qd7 20. Bd4 Bxd4 21. Qxd4 Nxd5 22. cxd5 a6 $11) 19... Qe8 20. Rfc1 Ne6 21. Nd5 b6 22. h4 Rab8 23. h5 Rb7 24. Rh1 f5 $5 {An active, interesting try.} 25. hxg6 $6 ({Better is} 25. Qd3 Qf7 26. hxg6 hxg6 27. Re2 $14) 25... Qxg6 $1 26. Nf4 $6 (26. exf5 Qxf5 27. Rh4 Rf8 28. Qe2 {was the alternative, forced try.}) 26... Nxf4+ 27. Bxf4 e5 $1 28. exf5 Qxf5 29. Be3 Rf7 {Black wrongly offered a draw. After 30.d1 or 30.f1, with 30...d5! he would have the upper hand.} 1/2-1/2


