1. Nf3 Nf6 2. c4 g6 3. g3 Bg7 4. Bg2 O-O 5. O-O d6 6. d4 Nc6 7. Nc3 Bf5 8. d5 Na5 9. Nd4 Bd7 10. b3 c5 {(D) } 11. dxc6 bxc6 (11... Nxc6 {is less ambitious:} 12. e3 (12. Bb2 Nxd4 13. Qxd4 Bc6 14. Nd5 Bxd5 15. Bxd5 Ne8 16. Qd2 Bxb2 17. Qxb2 Qc7 18. Rfd1 Nf6 19. Bf3 a5 20. Rd4 Qb6 21. Rad1 Rfc8 22. h4 h5 {Ruck,R-Gyimesi,Z/Sibenik 2006}) 12... a6 13. Bb2 Rc8 14. Nde2 Rb8 15. a4 $11 {Ruck,R-Nikolaidis,I/Panormo 2002}) 12. Bb2 ({Instead of the text-move, White has also tried: a)} 12. Bd2 Rb8 13. Rc1 c5 14. Nc2 Nc6 15. Ne3 Nb4 16. a3 Nc6 17. Ncd5 a5 18. Bc3 Nxd5 19. Nxd5 Be6 20. Nf6+ Bxf6 21. Bxf6 exf6 22. Bxc6 Qb6 23. Ba4 Rfd8 24. e4 Qb7 25. Re1 f5 26. exf5 Bxf5 27. Rc3 d5 {½-½ Smyslov,V-Gulko,B/Lvov 1978}) ({b)} 12. e4 c5 (12... Rb8 13. h3 c5 14. Nde2 Nc6 $11 {Janssen,R-Ikonnikov,V/Vlissingen 1998}) 13. Nc2 Rb8 14. h3 Qc8 15. g4 Nc6 16. Bd2 h5 17. f3 hxg4 18. hxg4 Nd4 $15 {Leveille,F-Fedorowicz,J/New York 1994}) ({c)} 12. Ba3 Qc8 13. Re1 Rb8 14. Qd2 Qa6 15. Nc2 Nb7 16. h3 Rfe8 17. Rac1 Rbd8 18. e4 Qa5 $11 {Sapunov,E-Neverov,V/St Petersburg 2003}) ({d)} 12. e3 Qc8 13. Nde2 Bh3 14. Bd2 Bxg2 15. Kxg2 Nb7 16. e4 Rd8 17. Rc1 Qd7 18. Bf4 Nc5 19. Qc2 Ne6 20. Rcd1 Nxf4+ 21. Nxf4 c5 22. Rfe1 {½-½ Kveinys,A-Dydyshko,V/Ustron 2006}) 12... Rb8 (12... Qc8 13. Qd2 Bh3 14. Rad1 Bxg2 15. Kxg2 Nb7 16. Na4 e5 17. Nc2 Qe6 18. Nb4 a5 19. Nd3 e4 20. Nf4 Qf5 {½-½ Nedilko,V-Nesteretz,A/Alushta 2006}) 13. Qd2 c5 ({Also not bad is} 13... Qb6 14. Rab1 Rfd8 15. e4 Nb7 16. h3 Nc5 17. Rbd1 a5 $11 {Skatchkov,P-Morozov,D//St Petersburg 2004}) 14. Ndb5 ({Or} 14. Nf3 Nc6 (14... Be6 $6 15. Nd1 Qb6 16. Ng5 Bc8 17. Ne3 $14 {Vyatkin,D-Sultangareev,M/Ufa 2004}) 15. Rfd1 Qa5 16. Rac1 Nb4 17. h3 Qb6 18. Ba1 a5 19. e4 Rfd8 20. Qe2 e5 21. Rb1 Be8 22. Nd5 Nbxd5 23. cxd5 a4 $11 {Marszalek,M-Daulyte,D/Krakow 2005}) 14... a6 $1 ({Accurate. Worse is} 14... Nc6 $6 15. Bxc6 $1 (15. Nd5 $2 Nxd5 16. Bxg7 Kxg7 17. Bxd5 Nb4 18. Nxa7 Nxd5 19. Qxd5 Qc7 20. Nb5 Bxb5 21. cxb5 Rxb5 $15 {Barcza,G-Gufeld,E/Leningrad 1967}) 15... Bxc6 16. Nxa7 Ba8 17. Nab5 Qd7 18. a4 Qh3 19. f3 Bh6 20. e3 Rfd8 21. Nd5 Nxd5 22. cxd5 $16 {Menk,R-Howell,J/Muenster 1994}) 15. Na3 Qb6 16. Rad1 Rfd8 17. Ba1 (17. Nd5 Nxd5 18. Bxg7 Kxg7 19. Bxd5 Nc6 $13) 17... Bc6 18. e4 $6 ({I think that White should play} 18. Nd5 Nxd5 19. cxd5 Bxa1 20. Rxa1 Bd7 $13) 18... e6 $1 {Now Black has fully controlled the central squares.} 19. Nc2 Ba8 20. Ne3 Nc6 $5 (20... Qb4 $11) 21. Ncd5 Nxd5 (21... exd5 $2 22. Bxf6 Bxf6 23. Nxd5 $18) 22. cxd5 Nd4 23. Nc4 (23. Nc2 e5 24. f4 f5 $1 $13) 23... Qc7 24. Rde1 Re8 25. Kh1 f5 $1 26. exf5 exd5 27. Ne3 Qf7 28. fxg6 hxg6 29. f4 Re4 $1 {A typical exchange sacrifice, aiming for full central control and attacking possibilities on the white king.} 30. f5 $1 (30. Bxe4 dxe4 {is very nice for Black.}) 30... Rbe8 31. f6 $6 (31. fxg6 Qxg6 32. Bxe4 dxe4 33. Rd1 Bc6 $44) 31... Bxf6 32. Bxe4 dxe4 33. Rf4 Qe6 34. Ref1 Bg7 35. Rf7 Be5 36. Ra7 {Now a series of time-trouble errors starts:} Nf3 $2 (36... d5 $1 $44) 37. Qc1 $1 Nd4 38. Rff7 Bc6 39. Ng2 $4 (39. Qf1 $1 Bb5 40. Ng4 $1 Nf5 41. Qh3 $18) 39... e3 $1 40. Qxe3 Qh3 $2 (40... Nf5 41. Bxe5 Bxg2+ 42. Kg1 Qxf7 $19) 41. Qf2 Nf5 $2 (41... Nf3 42. Rxf3 Bxa1 43. Rxa6 Bd4 44. Qf1 Bxf3 45. Qxf3 Qh6 46. Qd5+ $16) (41... Bd5 $1 42. Rae7 Rxe7 43. Rxe7 Nf3 $17) 42. Rh7 $2 (42. Bxe5 Rxe5 43. Kg1 Qg4 44. Rg7+ Kh8 45. Rh7+ Kg8 46. h3 $16) 42... Qxg2+ $2 (42... Qxh7 43. Rxh7 Bxa1 44. Rc7 Bd4 $19) 43. Qxg2 Bxg2+ 44. Kxg2 Bxa1 $17 45. Rhb7 Bf6 46. Rxa6 Be7 47. Rc6 Kf7 48. g4 Nh6 49. Rxd6 Nxg4 50. Rc6 Ra8 51. a4 Ra5 52. Rcc7 Ne3+ 53. Kf3 Nf5 54. Kf2 Ke6 55. Ra7 Rxa7 56. Rxa7 Kd5 57. Ra6 Bd6 58. h3 {Black's advantage is undeniable, as his two minor pieces are clearly superior to the white rook, in addition to his much more active king. Black must focus on the capture of the white b-pawn, so as to create a passed foot-soldier. In many lines the win comes in the form of a bishop & knight vs king ending.} g5 59. Rb6 Bg3+ 60. Kf3 Bc7 61. Rf6 (61. Rb7 Kc6) 61... Nd4+ 62. Kf2 (62. Kg4 Nxb3 63. Kxg5 $2 Bd8 $19) 62... Nxb3 63. Rf5+ Kd4 64. Rxg5 c4 65. Rb5 ({Or} 65. Ke2 Nc5 66. Rg4+ Kc3 67. h4 Kb3 68. h5 c3 69. h6 c2 70. Rg1 Nxa4 71. h7 Be5) 65... Nc5 66. h4 c3 67. Ke2 Kc4 68. h5 Nxa4 ({Black throws the win away, a win that was very close after} 68... Nb3 $1 69. Rg5 Bf4 70. Rg1 c2 71. Kf3 c1=Q 72. Rxc1+ Bxc1) 69. Rf5 Bb6 ({The alternative} 69... Nc5 70. h6 Nb3 71. h7 Nd4+ 72. Kf2 (72. Ke1 $4 Bg3+ 73. Kd1 Kd3 74. Rc5 Be5 {is winning for Black.}) 72... c2 73. h8=Q c1=Q 74. Qg8+ {is also leading to a draw.}) 70. h6 Bd4 $4 ({In terrible time pressure, Black gives away even the half point of the draw!} 70... c2 71. Kd2 Be3+ 72. Kxc2 Bxh6 {is not too difficult to find.}) 71. Rf4 $1 1-0


