1. Nf3 Nf6 2. g3 g6 3. Bg2 Bg7 4. O-O O-O 5. d4 d6 6. c4 Nc6 7. Nc3 Bf5 8. b3 Ne4 9. Bb2 Nxc3 10. Bxc3 Be4 11. Qd2 {(D) } d5 12. Rfd1 e6 13. e3 a5 (13... Qe7 14. Qe2 Rfd8 15. cxd5 exd5 16. Rac1 a6 17. Bb2 Na7 18. Bh3 Bxf3 19. Qxf3 c6 20. Bf1 Nc8 21. h4 a5 $11 {Ruck,R-Tolnai,T/Budapest 1995}) 14. Qe2 Qe7 15. Ne1 Bxg2 16. Kxg2 Nb8 (16... Rfd8 17. Nd3 Nb4 $11 (17... e5 $6 18. cxd5 Rxd5 19. Nxe5 Nxe5 20. dxe5 Rxd1 21. Rxd1 Bxe5 22. Bxe5 Qxe5 23. Qf3 Qb5 24. Rd5 $14)) 17. cxd5 exd5 18. Nd3 Re8 $11 19. b4 $2 (19. Qf3 c6 20. a4 $11) 19... axb4 $2 ({The "tactical"} 19... Nc6 20. Qb2 axb4 21. Nxb4 Nxb4 22. Bxb4 Qe4+ 23. Kg1 h5 $17 {was excellent for Black.}) 20. Nxb4 c6 21. a4 Na6 22. Nxa6 Rxa6 23. a5 h5 24. h4 Bf8 (24... c5 {was not bad either.}) 25. Rab1 Rd8 26. Rb3 {Now White has a fixed target on b7 to attack. The problem is that Black is lacking counterplay or targets and can only defend.} Qc7 27. Rdb1 Ra7 28. Rb6 Rd7 29. a6 bxa6 30. Rxa6 Rb7 $2 ({Black had to accept} 30... Rxa6 31. Qxa6 Rd6 32. Qb7 Qxb7 33. Rxb7 Re6 $11 {but he was trying to win on time against a lower rated opponent. Not a nice policy anyway!}) 31. Ba5 Qc8 32. Rc1 Rd6 33. Bb6 Re6 34. Rca1 Kg7 35. Ra8 Rb8 36. Qa6 Qxa6 37. R1xa6 Ree8 38. R8a7 Bd6 $2 (38... Rbc8 $14 {was the only move.}) 39. Bc7 $1 {Now White is winning. The rest was not that difficult:} Bxc7 40. Rxc7 Rb2 41. Raa7 Rxe3 42. Rxf7+ Kg8 43. Rg7+ Kf8 44. Rgf7+ Kg8 45. Rfc7 Re8 46. Rxc6 Rf8 47. Rxg6+ Kh8 48. Rh6+ Kg8 49. Rxh5 Rfxf2+ 50. Kh3 Rb5 51. Rg5+ Kf8 52. Rd7 1-0


