{Nigel Davies: 'Brynell probably decided that his 6.d3 was rather innocuous as he later turned to 6.Nxe5 against Hector. Indeed Black doesn't seem unduly troubled by it all.'} 1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 a6 4. Bxc6 dxc6 5. O-O Be7 $5 6. d3 Bf6 (6... f6 7. Nh4 $1 Be6 8. Nf5 Bf8 9. f4 exf4 10. Bxf4 g6 11. Ng3 Bg7 12. Nc3 Ne7 13. Qd2 Qd7 14. Bh6 $14) 7. Be3 ({Nigel Davies: 'After'} 7. d4 $5 {Nigel Davies: 'Black obtains a satisfactory position with'} Bg4 $1 8. dxe5 Qxd1 9. Rxd1 Bxe5 $11 {Nigel Davies: 'etc.'}) 7... Ne7 8. Nbd2 $146 ({Nigel Davies: 'Once again'} 8. d4 $6 {Nigel Davies: 'is answered by'} Bg4 {Nigel Davies: 'with Black getting a good game after'} 9. c3 (9. dxe5 Qxd1 10. Rxd1 Bxf3 11. gxf3 Bxe5 $15) 9... Bxf3 $1 10. gxf3 (10. Qxf3 exd4 11. cxd4 Bxd4 12. Rd1 c5 $17) 10... Ng6 $15 {Nigel Davies: 'with White's kingside pawn structure being badly compromised.'}) (8. h3) 8... Ng6 9. Nc4 Be6 $1 10. b3 $8 (10. Na5 $6 b6 $1 11. Nxc6 Qd6 12. d4 Bc4 {Nigel Davies: 'costs White material.'} (12... Qxc6 13. d5 Qd7 14. dxe6 Qxe6 $11) 13. dxe5 Qxc6 14. exf6 Bxf1 15. fxg7 Rg8 16. Kxf1 Rxg7 $15) 10... b6 11. a4 a5 ({Nigel Davies: 'Black could also play'} 11... c5 $1 $13 {Nigel Davies: '!' Nigel Davies: 'and meet'} 12. a5 $6 {Nigel Davies: 'with'} b5 13. Ncd2 Be7 { Bd6 Nigel Davies: 'followed by ...Bd6.'}) 12. Bd2 $1 Bxc4 13. bxc4 $5 (13. dxc4 c5 {Nigel Davies: 'is equal.'} 14. Bc3 c6 $11) 13... Be7 $1 14. Bc3 (14. Rb1 $6 Bc5 $15) 14... Bb4 $1 15. Bxb4 ({Nigel Davies: 'After'} 15. Bb2 $6 Qe7 16. d4 exd4 $1 (16... Bd6 $2 17. c5 $1 bxc5 18. dxe5 Nxe5 19. Nd2 $1 $16) 17. Nxd4 {Nigel Davies: 'Black can play the calm'} O-O $1 {Nigel Davies: 'as'} 18. Nxc6 (18. Nf5 $2 {Nigel Davies: 'is bad because of'} Qxe4 19. Nxg7 Nf4 20. f3 Qg6 21. g3 Rad8 22. Qb1 Rd2 $19 {Nigel Davies: 'etc.'}) 18... Qxe4 19. Nxb4 axb4 $15) 15... axb4 16. c5 $1 Qe7 $1 (16... bxc5 $2 {Nigel Davies: 'would be bad because of'} 17. Nd2 { Nc4, a5 Nigel Davies: 'intending to plant the knight on c4 and then advance the passed a-pawn.'}) 17. cxb6 cxb6 18. Nd2 $1 {Nigel Davies: 'Heading for the useful c4 square.'} (18. Qd2 O-O 19. Rfb1 c5 20. c3 bxc3 21. Qxc3 Qd6 { Nf4, Rfd8}) 18... O-O 19. Nc4 Ra6 20. Qd2 Rfa8 21. Rab1 $8 c5 22. g3 ({Nigel Davies: 'White could also play the immediate'} 22. c3 {Nigel Davies: 'with the game likely to fizzle out after'} bxc3 23. Qxc3 Nf4 $1 24. Qxe5 (24. Rfe1 Rd8 $1 25. Nxe5 Rd4 $1 26. Nf3 $8 Rxd3 27. Qc4 Ra8 $13) 24... Qxe5 25. Nxe5 Re8 $1 26. Nc4 Rxa4 27. Nxb6 Rd4 $11) 22... Rb8 $1 23. c3 (23. Ra1 Rba8 $1) 23... Rxa4 $8 (23... b5 $6 24. axb5 Rxb5 25. cxb4 cxb4 26. Rb3 $14) 24. cxb4 cxb4 25. Rb3 (25. Ne3 Qd6 $1 26. Nd5 Ne7 27. Nxb4 Rc8 $15) 25... Qc5 26. Rfb1 Rd8 $1 27. Ne3 (27. Rxb4 Rxb4 28. Qxb4 Qxb4 29. Rxb4 Rxd3 30. Rxb6 Rd8 $11) 27... h6 $138 28. Rc1 $5 Qd6 $1 29. Nf5 ({Nigel Davies: 'After'} 29. Nd5 $6 Ne7 30. Rxb4 Rxb4 31. Nxb4 b5 $15 {Nigel Davies: 'the passed b-pawn gives Black a slight edge.'}) 29... Qd7 30. Rxb4 Rxb4 ({Nigel Davies: 'After'} 30... Rxb4 31. Qxb4 b5 32. Rc3 {Nigel Davies: 'it's difficult for Black to improve his position.'}) 1/2-1/2


