1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. d4 exd4 4. Nxd4 Bb4+ 5. c3 Be7 6. Bf4 d6 (6... Nf6 7. e5 Nd5 8. Bg3 Nxd4 9. Qxd4 c6 10. Bc4 Nb6 11. Bb3 O-O 12. Nd2 d5 13. exd6 Bf6 14. Qd3 Re8+ 15. Ne4 Bf5 16. f3 Nd7 17. O-O $16 {1-0 Palac,M-Djuric,S/Yerevan 1996 (28)}) 7. c4 $146 (7. Bb5 Bd7 8. Qa4 Ne5 9. Bxd7+ Qxd7 10. Qxd7+ Nxd7 11. Nd2 Nc5 12. Ke2 Nf6 13. Nf5 Bf8 14. f3 g6 15. Nd4 Bg7 $11 {0-1 Brulic,D-Loncar,R/Zadar 1998 (68)}) 7... Bf6 8. Be3 Nge7 9. Nc3 O-O {It can be concluded, that black has solved the opening problems. He has even slight advantage in development.} 10. Be2 Bxd4 11. Bxd4 f5 ({Also possible} 11... Nxd4 12. Qxd4 Nc6 {following by f7-f5 with equality.}) 12. Bf3 Be6 ({Comes into consideration} 12... f4 13. c5 Be6) 13. c5 fxe4 $6 ({More tempting was} 13... Nxd4 14. Qxd4 Nc6) 14. Bxe4 d5 15. Bc2 Bf5 16. Bb3 Kh8 17. O-O Nxd4 18. Qxd4 c6 $11 19. Rae1 Ng6 20. Re3 Qd7 21. Bd1 $1 Rae8 22. Rxe8 Qxe8 23. Bh5 Qe7 24. Ne2 Qg5 $6 {Black should avoid the exchange of his knight.} (24... Ne5 $142 $11) 25. Bxg6 Bxg6 26. Qc3 Re8 27. Nd4 $14 {[%csl Gd4]} Qf6 28. f3 h6 29. g3 h5 30. Kf2 h4 31. Re1 hxg3+ 32. hxg3 Rxe1 33. Kxe1 Qe5+ 34. Kf2 Qh5 $6 35. Ne6 Qh2+ 36. Ke3 Qh6+ 37. Nf4 Bf7 38. Qe5 Qh1 39. Kf2 Qc1 40. Qd4 $16 {[%csl Gd4,Gf4]} Kg8 41. g4 b6 42. cxb6 axb6 43. Ne2 Qc2 44. Qxb6 c5 45. Qb8+ Kh7 46. Qb3 Qg6 47. Qb7 d4 48. Nf4 Qc2+ 49. Kg3 Bxa2 50. Nh5 Qg6 51. Qa7 d3 52. Qxc5 (52. Qxa2 $2 Qd6+ {[%csl Gd3][%cal Gd3d2]}) 52... Qf7 53. Qd4 Bc4 54. Nf4 $18 Qc7 55. Kf2 g5 56. Nxd3 Qh2+ 57. Ke1 Bf7 58. Ne5 Be8 59. b3 Qc2 60. Qd3+ Qxd3 61. Nxd3 Kg7 62. Kd2 Kf6 63. Ke3 Bb5 64. Nc5 1-0


