1. Nf3 Nf6 2. c4 g6 3. g3 Bg7 4. Bg2 O-O 5. O-O d6 6. Nc3 Nc6 7. d4 Bf5 8. d5 Na5 9. Nd2 {(D) } ({A little bit passive continuation, in comparison with} 9. Nd4 {but with a lot of "venom".}) 9... c6 $1 10. e4 ({A critical continuation is} 10. b4 {although Black seems to be doing fine after} Nxc4 (10... Nxd5 {is not bad either:} 11. cxd5 Bxc3 12. e4 Bxa1 13. exf5 Bg7 (13... cxd5 14. bxa5 Bg7 (14... e6 15. fxe6 fxe6 16. Nb3 Bg7 17. Nd4 Bxd4 18. Qxd4 Qxa5 19. Bb2 e5 20. Bxd5+ Kg7 21. Qe4 $16 {Nielsen,U-Hvenekilde,J/Denmark 1993}) 15. Nb3 (15. Bxd5 $5) 15... gxf5 16. Qxd5 e6 17. Qxb7 d5 18. Ba3 Re8 19. Rc1 $14 {Pogosian,M-Mokriy,A/Minsk 2006}) 14. Qe2 cxd5 15. bxa5 gxf5 16. Bxd5 Qxa5 17. Bxb7 Rae8 18. Nf3 e6 19. Ba6 Rb8 20. Bd3 Rfc8 21. Ng5 h6 22. Nh3 Qe5 23. Qf3 Rc3 {½-½ Jirovsky,M-Rasik,V/Czech Rep. 1993}) 11. Nxc4 Nxd5 12. Nxd5 Bxa1 13. Bh6 Bg7 14. Bxg7 Kxg7 15. Nde3 Be6 16. a4 Bxc4 17. Nxc4 d5 18. Nd2 Qd6 $11 {Nielsen,P-Nataf,I/Reykjavik 2004}) 10... Bg4 {(D) } 11. Qa4 ({This looks better than White's main alternatives: a)} 11. Qc2 cxd5 12. cxd5 Rc8 13. Re1 b5 14. a3 Bd7 (14... e6 15. Qd3 exd5 16. Nxb5 Re8 $13 {Jussupow,A-Gulko,B/Reykjavik 1990}) 15. h3 e6 16. Qd3 a6 17. dxe6 Bxe6 $15 {Hassan,A-Maslak,K/Olomouc 2005}) ({b)} 11. f3 Bd7 12. dxc6 (12. Re1 cxd5 13. cxd5 Rc8 14. Nf1 b5 15. Qe2 b4 $15 {Granda Zuniga,J-Mendoza Nieto,J/Burriana 1990}) 12... Nxc6 13. Rb1 a6 14. Kh1 b5 15. cxb5 axb5 16. Nxb5 Nb4 (16... Rxa2 $15) 17. a4 Qb8 18. Nc3 Rc8 19. Ra1 d5 $13 20. Ndb1 $2 d4 21. Ne2 Nc2 22. Ra2 e5 23. f4 Ng4 {Szmetan,J-Valerga,D/Argentina 2000}) 11... Bd7 $5 ({Of course Black can immediately play} 11... cxd5 12. cxd5 (12. exd5 $6 Rc8 13. Nb3 Nxc4 14. Qxa7 Qd7 15. Nd2 Ne5 16. Qe3 Bh3 17. Bxh3 Qxh3 $17 {Jacobsen,B-Hvenekilde,J/Aarhus 1981}) 12... Bd7 13. Qb4 Qb6 14. Qxb6 axb6 15. a4 Rfc8 16. Ra3 Ng4 17. Bh3 Ne5 18. Bxd7 Nxd7 $11 {Jasnikowski,Z-Malisauskas,V/Katowice 1993}) 12. Qa3 $5 (12. Nb3 Nxb3 13. Qxb3 Rb8 14. Be3 Qa5 $11) 12... cxd5 13. cxd5 Rc8 14. Nb3 Nc4 $5 (14... Nxb3 15. Qxb3 Qa5 16. Be3 Rc7 $11) 15. Qxa7 (15. Qb4 $2 b5 16. Nd2 a5 17. Qb3 a4 18. Qd1 Ne5 $17) 15... b5 16. Re1 $2 ({A must is} 16. f3 b4 17. Nd1 Bb5 18. Re1 e6 $44) 16... Ng4 $1 17. h3 Nge5 18. Rd1 Rc7 $1 19. Qa6 (19. Qd4 Nxb2 $1 20. Bxb2 Nc4) 19... Qb8 $1 {The coming 20...a7 forced White to resign.} 0-1


