1. c4 {Grivas,E Grivas,E Grivas,E Nigel Davies} Nf6 2. Nc3 d5 3. cxd5 Nxd5 4. Nf3 g6 5. Qa4+ $5 {* Nigel Davies: '!?'} c6 $5 {Nigel Davies: '!?'} ({a)} 5... Bd7 6. Qh4 (6. Qb3 Nb6 7. d4 Be6 8. Qc2 Bg7 9. e4 Bg4 10. Ne5 Bxe5 11. dxe5 Nc6 12. Bb5 Bd7 13. Bxc6 Bxc6 14. Be3 $14 {Gelfand,B-Shirov,A/Dagomys 2008}) 6... Nxc3 7. dxc3 e5 8. Bg5 Be7 9. e4 Nc6 10. Bc4 h6 11. Bxe7 Qxe7 12. Qg3 $14 {Kramnik,V-Ivanchuk,V/Las Palmas 1996.}) ({b)} 5... Nc6 6. Ne5 Ndb4 (6... Nb6 $2 7. Nxc6 Nxa4 8. Nxd8 Nxc3 9. Nxf7 $16 {Krasenkow,M-Azmaiparashvili,Z/Groningen 1997}) (6... Nxc3 7. bxc3 Bd7 8. Nxd7 Qxd7 9. Rb1 $14 {Damljanovic,B-Prada Rubin,F/La Coruna 1998}) 7. a3 Nc2+ (7... Bg7 8. axb4 Bxe5 9. b5 Nb8 10. e3 O-O 11. d4 Bg7 12. Be2 c6 13. O-O $14 {Ionov,S-Gubanov,A/St.Petersburg 1997}) 8. Qxc2 Nxe5 9. d4 $1 Nd7 (9... Qxd4 $2 10. Nb5 $18) 10. Bf4 c6 11. Rd1 $14 {Kortcnoi,V-Berkes,F/Paks 2007.}) 6. Qd4 $1 (6. Nxd5 {(Nigel Davies) seems to be a simpler and more economical choice, my preference being for White because of his central pawn majority.}) 6... f6 (6... Nf6 $6 {Ü 12/23} 7. Qxd8+ Kxd8 8. e4 (8. d4 b6 (8... Bf5 9. Ng5 Ke8 10. e4 Bd7 11. Bc4 e6 12. e5 Nd5 13. Nge4 h6 14. Bd2 Be7 15. O-O $16 {Pachman,L-Beggi,P/Reggio Emilia 1975}) 9. e4 Nfd7 10. Bc4 Ke8 11. Bf4 Ba6 12. Bb3 e6 13. O-O-O $16 {Alekhine,A-Rellstab,L/Kemeri 1937}) 8... Nbd7 9. d4 Bg7 10. Bc4 e6 11. O-O b5 12. Bd3 a5 13. Bf4 Ba6 14. Rfe1 $16 {Volzhin,A-Murawski,G/Wisla 1998.}) (6... Rg8 {Ü 32/18}) 7. e4 {(D) } e5 $1 ({a)} 7... Nb6 $2 8. Qxd8+ Kxd8 9. d4 Bg4 10. Be3 N8d7 11. O-O-O $16 {Milov,V-Zollbrecht,J/Biel 1998.}) ({b)} 7... Nc7 $2 8. Qxd8+ Kxd8 9. d4 Bg4 10. Be3 Nd7 11. Be2 Ke8 12. O-O $16 {Petursson,M-Fries Nielsen,J/Graz 1978.}) ({c)} 7... Nxc3 $2 8. Qxc3 $1 e5 {Nigel Davies: 'is difficult for Black after'} (8... Bg4 $6 9. d4 Bxf3 10. gxf3 a5 11. Be3 e5 12. O-O-O $18 {Savchenko,S-Roeber,B/Gelsenkirchen 1999}) 9. Bc4 {Nigel Davies: 'because he'll have trouble getting his king to safety and meanwhile White can open 