1. d4 Nf6 2. Nf3 g6 3. c4 Bg7 4. g3 O-O 5. Bg2 d6 6. O-O Nc6 7. d5 Na5 8. Qa4 {(D) } c5 ({Black's main alternative} 8... b6 {is a good and playable one:} 9. Bd2 (9. Nd4 $6 Bd7 (9... Nd7 10. Rd1 Ne5 11. f4 $6 (11. Qc2 Bd7 12. b3 $11) 11... Bd7 12. Qc2 c5 13. dxc6 Nexc6 14. Nxc6 Nxc6 15. Be3 Rc8 $15 {Diaz,N-Della Morte,P/Buenos Aires 2006}) 10. Qc2 Nxd5 $5 11. Bxd5 c6 $15 (11... Bxd4 12. Bxa8 Qxa8 $44)) (9. Nbd2 Bd7 10. Qc2 c6 $36) 9... Ne4 $1 10. Qc2 Nxd2 11. Nbxd2 c5 $11 (11... Nb7 $5 12. Rab1 a5 13. b3 Nc5 14. a3 Bd7 15. b4 axb4 16. axb4 Na4 $11)) 9. Bd2 ({Black should feel fine after} 9. dxc6 Nxc6 10. Nc3 (10. Rd1 Bd7 11. Qa3 Rc8 12. Nc3 a5 13. Qb3 a4 14. Qxa4 Na5 15. Qc2 Nxc4 $11 {D'Amore,C-Sepp,O/Turin OL 2006}) 10... Qa5 (10... Nd7 11. Qc2 Nc5 12. Be3 Bf5 13. Qd2 Ne4 14. Nxe4 Bxe4 15. Bh6 Bxh6 16. Qxh6 Bxf3 17. exf3 Nd4 18. Qd2 Qb6 $11 {Kruml,D-Sevcik,V/Moravia 2003}) 11. Qb3 Qh5 12. Nd5 Nxd5 (12... e5 $6 13. Rd1 $14 {Dabrowski,R-Lang,T/Untergrombach 2003}) 13. cxd5 Nd4 14. Nxd4 Bxd4 15. e4 a5 $11) 9... b6 10. Bc3 Bd7 {(D) } ({Now, there are many ways for Black to proceed: a)} 10... Rb8 11. Nbd2 e5 (11... Ng4 $6 12. Bxg7 Kxg7 13. Qc2 b5 14. cxb5 Rxb5 15. h3 Nf6 16. e4 Ba6 17. Rfe1 Qb6 18. b3 c4 19. Bf1 cxb3 20. Qb2 Rc5 21. Bxa6 Qxa6 22. axb3 Qb6 23. b4 Nb7 $16 (23... Rb8 $2 24. Qa2 {1-0 Strikovic,A-Romero Garcia,M/Seville 2001})) 12. Qc2 (12. dxe6 fxe6 13. Rad1 Bd7 14. Qc2 e5 $6 (14... Bc6 $11) 15. Ng5 Bf5 16. Nge4 Nc6 17. e3 $14 {Tibensky,R-Socko,B/Senec 1998}) (12. Ne1 Nh5 13. Bxa5 bxa5 {Black is not afraid of this weakness on a5, because the b  and the  will fully compensate for it.} 14. Nb3 Bd7 15. Qxa5 Qxa5 16. Nxa5 Rxb2 17. e4 Rfb8 18. Nd3 R2b6 $15 {Vavrak,P-Blehm,P/Mureck 1998}) (12. e4 Ne8 (12... Nh5 {is usually more active in this type of position.}) 13. Rfe1 f5 14. exf5 gxf5 15. Qc2 Bf6 16. a3 Ng7 17. b4 Nb7 {(the  is rather bad on b7, but White has to take into account that after a possible 1...cxb4 2.axb4 a5 it may come back)} 18. Nb3 Qc7 19. Nfd2 Bd7 20. Qb2 cxb4 21. axb4 a5 $13 {Navrotescu,C-Nevednichy,V/Predeal 1997}) 12... Nb7 13. Ne1 Qe7 14. e4 h5 {(this is a well-known motif in such positions, intending to undermine the threat f2-f4)} 15. f4 h4 16. Qd3 hxg3 17. hxg3 Ng4 18. Nc2 f5 19. Rae1 Bd7 20. exf5 Bxf5 21. Be4 Qd7 $13 {Tibensky,R-Lanka,Z/Czechia 2001}) ({b)} 10... Qd7 $5 $146 11. Qc2 (11. Qxd7 Bxd7 12. Nbd2 Ne8 13. Bxg7 Kxg7 14. e4 f6 15. a3 b5 16. cxb5 Bxb5 17. Rfc1 Nb7 $132) 11... Qf5 12. Qxf5 (12. Qc1 Qh5 13. Nbd2 Bh3 $13 {Angel Acosta,J-Garcia Luque,A/Spain 1999} (13... Bh6 14. Qc2)) 12... Bxf5 13. Nbd2 (13. Nfd2 $5 Bxb1 (13... Rae8 $5 14. Na3 Bd7 $13) 14. Raxb1 Nd7 15. Bxg7 Kxg7 $14 {White certainly has a spatial advantage, but in many cases White's  remains passive.'}) 13... Ne4 14. Bxg7 Kxg7 15. Nxe4 Bxe4 16. Nd2 Bxg2 (16... Bf5 17. a4 $1 $14) 17. Kxg2 Rab8 18. a4 e6 19. e4 (19. dxe6 fxe6 {breaks the balance at least.}) 19... Rfe8 $11 {Kutirov,R-Atalik,S/Budapest 1999}) ({c)} 10... Qe8 11. Qxe8 Nxe8 12. Nfd2 Nc7 13. Rc1 Bd7 14. e3 Rfb8 15. a3 a6 16. Bf1 Bxc3 {½-½ Panno,O-Roselli Mailhe,B/Pinamar 2001}) ({d)} 10... e5 11. dxe6 (11. Nbd2 {is certainly possible, but then Black has spared having to play b8.}) 11... fxe6 (11... Bxe6 12. Ng5 Bd7 13. Qd1 Rb8 14. Qxd6 Nxc4 $11 {Garcia Palermo,C-Avrukh,B/Turin OL 2006}) 12. Bxa5 bxa5 13. Nc3 Rb8 14. Qc2 Bb7 {Black's flexible  and his  compensate for the weaknesses on the .} 15. Rad1 Qe7 $13 {Scarella,E-Zarnicki,P/Villa Martelli 1998}) 11. Qc2 b5 {(D) } ({Again Black has some fair alternatives at his disposal: a)} 11... Nxc4 $5 12. Bxf6 Bxf6 13. Qxc4 Bxb2 14. Nc3 (14. Nbd2 b5 (14... Bxa1 15. Rxa1 b5 16. Qf4 {- 14...b5} Qa5 $13) 15. Qh4 (15. Qf4 Bxa1 16. Rxa1 {- 14...b5}) 15... Bxa1 16. Ng5 (16. Rxa1 Kg7) 16... h5 17. Rxa1 Qa5 18. Ngf3 Qc3 $13 {Sorokin,M-Valerga,D/Buenos Aires 1997}) 14... Bxa1 15. Rxa1 a6 $13) ({b)} 11... Bf5 12. Qc1 {and now: b1)} b5 ({b2)} 12... a6 13. b3 Rb8 (13... b5 14. Nbd2 Rb8 {- 13...b8}) 14. Nbd2 b5 {- 13...b8} 15. Re1 e5 ({b21)} 15... b4 16. Bb2 e5 17. a3 ({b211)} 17. e4 Bc8 (17... Bd7 18. a3 $5 Qb6 19. axb4 Nb7 $1 $11) 18. a3 Nd7 $11) ({b212)} 17. dxe6 Bxe6 18. Ng5 Re8 19. Qd1 Qc7 $11) 17... Bh6 18. e3 Ne4 19. Nxe4 Bxe4 20. Nd2 Bxg2 21. Kxg2 $14) ({b22)} 15... bxc4 16. bxc4 Ne4 17. Bxg7 Kxg7 18. Nh4 Nxd2 19. Nxf5+ gxf5 20. Qxd2 $14 {Bagaturov,G-Thomas,O/La Fere 2006}) 16. dxe6 (16. e4 Bd7 $13) 16... Bxe6 17. Ng5 bxc4 $2 (17... b4 18. Nxe6 fxe6 19. Bb2 Qc7 $11) 18. Nxe6 fxe6 19. bxc4 $2 (19. Qa3 $1 Nb7 20. Qxa6 $16) 19... Qc7 20. Qa3 Nc6 21. Qxa6 Nb4 22. Bxb4 cxb4 $44 {Mchedlishvili,M-Milov,V/Moscow 2002}) ({b3)} 12... Rb8 13. Re1 (13. Nbd2) 13... e5 (13... Nxc4 $5 14. Bxf6 Bxf6 15. Qxc4 Bxb2) 14. dxe6 Bxe6 15. b3 d5 $1 16. cxd5 Bxd5 17. Qb2 Qe7 18. Na3 Ba8 19. Rad1 Rfd8 20. Nc2 Nh5 21. Bxg7 Nxg7 $11 {Schuh,H-Howell,J/Germany 1992}) 13. cxb5 Rb8 14. Nbd2 Rxb5 15. Re1 e6 16. e4 Bg4 17. h3 Bxf3 18. Bxf3 exd5 19. exd5 c4 20. Bg2 (20. Qd1 $5) 20... Nxd5 21. Bxg7 Kxg7 22. Nxc4 Rc5 23. Bxd5 Rxd5 24. b4 Nxc4 25. Qxc4 Qg5 26. Rad1 Rxd1 27. Rxd1 Qe5 28. Qc7 Qe2 29. Qxd6 Qxa2 30. Qd4+ Kg8 $11 {Kacheishvili,G-Bologan,V/Stratton Mountain 1999}) 12. cxb5 Bxb5 {(D) } ({Alternatives are: a)} 12... Nxd5 $5 13. Bxg7 Kxg7 14. Nfd2 $1 (14. Ne1 e6 15. Nc3 Rb8 16. Bxd5 exd5 17. Nxd5 Bxb5 $11 {Choma,E-Della Morte,P/Buenos Aires 2003}) 14... Nf6 $5 (14... e6 15. Nc3 Nb4 (15... Rb8 16. Nxd5 exd5 17. Bxd5 Bxb5 18. Qc3+ f6 19. Rfe1 $16) 16. Qc1 Rc8 17. a3 f5 18. Qb1 Nd5 19. Nxd5 exd5 20. Bxd5 Bxb5 21. b4 $14 {Bodnar,O-Dumitrescu,D/Baile Tusnad 1999}) 15. Bxa8 Qxa8 16. Nc3 $1 (16. Re1 Bxb5 $44) (16. f3 Bxb5 17. Nc3 Bd7 18. e4 Nc6 19. Nc4 Nd4 20. Qd3 d5 21. Nxd5 Nxd5 22. exd5 Qxd5 23. Rf2 Bc6 $44 {Izquierdo,D-Crosa Coll,M/Montevideo 2000}) 16... Bh3 17. e4 Bxf1 18. Kxf1 a6 $44 {with a well-known Benko Gambit type of motif.}) ({b)} 12... Rb8 13. e4 Bxb5 14. Rd1) 13. Rd1 ({More common is} 13. Na3 $1 a6 (13... Qb6 $6 14. Rfd1 Bd7 15. e4 Bg4 16. Qa4 Nb7 17. e5 $1 Bxf3 18. Bxf3 Ne8 19. Nc4 Qc7 20. Re1 $16 {Badea,B-Itkis,V/Romania 2000}) 14. Rfd1 Nd7 15. Bxg7 Kxg7 16. e4 Kg8 17. h4 $14 {Abramovic,B-Pikula,D/Nis 1996}) 13... Nc4 $1 (13... Qb6 14. e4 (14. Na3 $1 {transposes to the previous note.}) 14... Rac8 $6 (14... Rab8 15. Na3 Ba6 16. Qa4 Nb7 17. Nd2 {Slowly but surely White takes control over the vital × c4.} Be2 18. Re1 Qa6 19. Qxa6 Bxa6 20. Nac4 Nd7 21. e5 Nxe5 22. Nxe5 Bxe5 23. Bxe5 dxe5 24. Rxe5 $14 {Gaprindashvili,V-Efimenko,Z/Alushta 2000}) 15. e5 Nh5 16. Bh3 Rc7 17. Na3 $16 {Braun,S-Hofstetter,H/Bayern 2003}) 14. e4 Nb6 {Black improves his previously badly placed knight.} 15. a4 Ba6 16. h3 (16. a5 $5 Nbd7 17. e5 dxe5 $5 (17... Ng4 18. e6 Nde5 19. Nxe5 Nxe5 20. h3 $14) 18. Nxe5 Nxe5 19. Bxe5 Rc8 20. d6 exd6 21. Bxd6 Re8 22. Nc3 Nd7 $13) 16... Rc8 17. a5 (17. Na3 Re8) 17... Nbd7 18. Nbd2 (18. e5 Ne8 (18... dxe5 19. Nxe5 Nxe5 20. Bxe5 Ne8 $11) 19. e6 fxe6 20. Ng5 Nc7 21. Bxg7 Kxg7 $13) 18... Qc7 19. Bf1 Bxf1 20. Kxf1 e6 $1 21. Nc4 (21. dxe6 fxe6 22. Ng5 Rce8 $13) 21... exd5 22. exd5 a6 23. Qa4 Rfe8 (23... Ne8 $6 24. Re1) (23... Nb8 $6 24. Ra3 { b3-b6}) 24. Qc6 $5 Qxc6 $6 ({Black needs to keep the queens on the board, as the white king is not absolutely safe. He should play the stronger} 24... Qa7 $1 25. Qxd6 $2 (25. Qa4 Ne4 $11) 25... Bf8 (25... Ne4 $2 26. Qf4 Bxc3 27. bxc3 Nxc3 28. Nd6 $18) 26. Qf4 Re4 27. Qc1 Rxc4 28. Nd2 Bh6 29. f4 Bxf4 30. gxf4 Rxf4+ $19) 25. dxc6 Rxc6 26. Nxd6 $14 Rb8 27. g4 (27. Rd2 $5 Bh6 28. Rd3 Bf8 29. Rad1 $14) 27... Rc7 28. Rd2 Ne8 $6 ({Much better was} 28... Nf8 $1 29. Re1 Ne6 30. Be5 $1 Rb3 (30... Nd7 31. Nxf7 $1 (31. Bg3 Ra7 (31... Rxb2 32. Rxb2 Bxb2 33. Nc4 Rb7 34. Rb1 Rb4 35. Nxb2 c4 36. Ne5 $18) 32. Nxf7 Kxf7 33. Bxb8 Nxb8 34. Rd6 $14) 31... Nxe5 32. N7xe5 $16) 31. Bxf6 Rxf3 (31... Bxf6 32. Ne8 Rxf3 33. Rxe6 fxe6 34. Nxc7 $16) 32. Bxg7 Nxg7 33. Ne4 Ne6 34. g5 $14) 29. Re1 $1 Bxc3 (29... Nxd6 30. Rxd6 Ra7 31. Re7 Rbb7 32. Re8+ Nf8 33. g5 $16) 30. bxc3 Kf8 31. Nxf7 $1 (31. Nxe8 Rxe8 32. Rxe8+ Kxe8 33. Rd6 Ra7 34. Rc6 $16) 31... Kxf7 32. Rxd7+ (32. Ng5+ $2 Kg8 $17) 32... Rxd7 33. Ne5+ Ke7 34. Nc6+ Kf8 (34... Kd6 35. Nxb8 Re7 36. Rd1+ Kc7 37. Nxa6+ Kc6 38. Rb1 $18) (34... Kf7 35. Nxb8 Rd3 36. Re3 Rxe3 (36... Rd1+ 37. Kg2 Ra1 38. Nc6 $18) 37. fxe3 Nc7 38. Ke2 $18) 35. Nxb8 Rd6 36. Re5 c4 37. Rc5 Rd1+ 38. Ke2 Ra1 39. Nxa6 Nd6 40. Nb4 Ke7 (40... Ke8 41. a6 {1-0 (42) Tregubov,P (2490)-Grivas,E (2495) Heraklion 1995 CBM 122 [Grivas,Efstratios]}) 41. a6 Kd7 42. f3 1-0


