1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 b6 4. g3 Ba6 5. Qb3 Nc6 6. Nbd2 Bb7 7. e4 Na5 ({As usual Black has some alternatives at his disposal: a)} 7... d5 8. cxd5 exd5 9. e5 Ne4 10. Bd3 {and now: a4)} Bb4 ({a1)} 10... Qd7 11. O-O Nb4 12. Bb1 c5 13. Re1 cxd4 14. Nxe4 dxe4 15. Bxe4 O-O-O 16. Bg5 Bxe4 17. Rxe4 $18 {Lautier,J-Tukmakov,V/Odessa 2006.}) ({a2)} 10... Nb4 $5 11. Bb1 (11. Bb5+ $5 c6 12. Be2 c5 13. a3 Nc6 (13... c4 14. Nxc4 dxc4 15. Bxc4 Nd5 16. Bb5+ Ke7 17. O-O $16) 14. O-O (14. Nxe4 dxe4 15. Ng5 Qe7 16. dxc5 h6 17. Nxe4 Qxe5 18. Qa4 Bxc5 19. Nxc5 bxc5 20. Qb5 (20. Bf4 Qxb2 21. O-O O-O) 20... O-O) 14... Be7 15. Nxe4 (15. dxc5 Nxc5 16. Qc2 Ne6 17. Nb3 Rc8 18. Qf5 g6 19. Qh3) 15... dxe4 16. d5 exf3 17. Bb5 Qc7 18. Qxf3 Rc8 19. Rd1 O-O 20. dxc6 Bxc6 21. Bxc6 Qxc6 22. Qxc6 Rxc6 23. Rd7 Re6 24. Rxa7 Rxe5 25. Bf4 Re6 26. Rd1 Bf6 27. b3 Bd4 $11) 11... c5 12. O-O Rc8 13. a3 (13. Re1 c4 14. Qe3 Nd3 15. Bxd3 cxd3 16. Qxd3 Be7 17. Nxe4 dxe4 18. Rxe4 Qd5 19. Re3 Bg5 20. Re1 Be7 $11) (13. dxc5 Bxc5 14. Nxe4 dxe4 15. Rd1 Qe7 16. Ng5 Nd3 17. Bxd3 exd3 18. Qxd3 h6 19. Ne4 O-O 20. Nd6 Rcd8 21. Bf4 Ba8 $44) 13... c4 14. Qe3 Nd3 15. Bxd3 cxd3 16. Qxd3 Be7 17. Ne1 O-O 18. f3 Ng5 19. Nb3 $14 {Stohl,I-Hracek,Z/Czech Rep. 1998.}) ({a3)} 10... f5 $5 11. O-O (11. exf6 Qxf6 12. Qxd5 $5 (12. O-O O-O-O 13. Nxe4 dxe4 14. Bxe4 Nxd4 15. Bxb7+ Kxb7 16. Nxd4 Rxd4 17. Be3 Rb4 18. Qd5+ Qc6 19. Qd2 Bd6 $11) 12... Nxd2 13. Bxd2 Rd8 14. Qe4+ Be7 15. d5 $1 Na5 16. Bb5+ Kf8 17. Bg5 Bxd5 18. Qe3 Qe6 19. O-O Qxe3 20. fxe3 Bxg5 21. Nxg5+ Ke7 22. e4 Bg8 23. Rac1 c5 24. b3 h6 25. Nf3 $14) 11... Qd7 12. a3 Nd8 13. Qd1 Ne6 14. b4 O-O-O 15. Nb3 (15. Bb2 $5 Kb8 16. Nh4 g6 17. f3 N4g5 18. f4 (18. Ng2) 18... Ne4 19. b5 Be7 20. Ndf3 $14) 15... g5 16. Ne1 h5 17. f3 h4 18. g4 (18. fxe4 $2 fxe4 19. gxh4 exd3 20. h5 Ba6 21. Nxd3 Bc4 22. Be3 Qh7 $17) 18... Nf4 (18... f4 19. Qc2 Kb8 20. b5 $13) 19. Bxf4 (19. gxf5 $5 Qxf5 20. Ra2 $14) 19... gxf4 20. h3 fxg4 21. fxg4 Kb8 {½-½ Riazantsev,A-Sadvakasov,D/Moscow 2005.}) 11. O-O O-O (11... Bxd2 12. Bxd2 O-O 13. Qc2 f5 14. Bb5 Ne7 15. b4 c6 16. Be2 Ng6 17. a4 Rc8 18. Qb2 Rc7 19. b5 c5 20. dxc5 Nxd2 21. Nxd2 bxc5 22. f4 $14 {Nielsen,P-Sasikiran,K)/Copenhagen 2003}) 12. Rd1 Bxd2 (12... Ng5 13. Nxg5 Qxg5 14. Nf3 Qh5 15. Bf4 $14 {Lerner,K-Novikov,I/Yalta 1982}) 13. Bxd2 Kh8 (13... a5 14. Rac1 Rc8 15. a3 $1 (15. Qa4 Ne7 16. b4 axb4 17. Bxb4 c5 18. dxc5 bxc5 19. Qa7 cxb4 20. Qxb7 Nc3 21. Re1 Rb8 22. Qa7 {½-½ Riazantsev,A-Ivanov,S/St Petersburg 2005}) 15... Kh8 16. Bb5 Ne7 17. Be2 Ba8 18. Bg5 h6 19. Bxe7 Qxe7 20. Nh4 Rb8 21. Bg4 c5 22. f3 Ng5 23. Nf5 Qd8 24. Nd6 $16 {Dydyshko,V-Maiorov,N/Minsk 2007}) 14. Rac1 (14. Bf4 f6 15. exf6 Rxf6 16. Rac1 $14 {Lautier,J-Sasikiran,K/Corsica 2005}) (14. Be3 f6 15. Bb5 Na5 16. Qc2 Nc4 $1 $13 {Karpov,A-Lautier,J/Cap d'Agde 2003}) 14... f6 15. Bf4 Na5 16. Qc2 Rc8 17. b4 Nc6 18. Qa4 $16 {Sargissian,G-Zhang Zhong/Internet 2004.}) ({b)} 7... Be7 8. Bd3 (8. Bg2 O-O 9. O-O d6 (9... d5 $5 10. cxd5 exd5 11. e5 Ne4 12. Re1 f5 $13) 10. d5 Ne5 11. Nxe5 dxe5 12. Qc2 exd5 13. exd5 Qd7 14. b3 c6 15. dxc6 Bxc6 16. Ne4 Nxe4 17. Bxe4 f5 18. Bxc6 Qxc6 19. Bb2 e4 20. Rad1 Rae8 21. Rd5 Bc5 $11 {Aronian,L-Schmaltz,R/Internet 2004}) 8... O-O 9. O-O d5 10. cxd5 exd5 11. e5 Ne4 12. Re1 (12. Nxe4 dxe4 13. Bxe4 Nxd4 14. Qe3 (14. Bxh7+ $2 Kxh7 15. Qd3+ Kh8 16. Nxd4 c5 $19) 14... Nxf3+ 15. Qxf3 Bxe4 16. Qxe4 Qd7 $11) 12... f5 13. exf6 (13. Nxe4 $2 fxe4 14. Bxe4 Na5 $19) 13... Nxf6 14. a3 (14. Nf1 Kh8 {½-½ Leitao,R-Mareco,S/Santos 2008}) 14... Kh8 15. Qd1 $1 (15. Qc2 $6 Ne4 16. Bb5 Qd6 (16... Nxd4 $2 17. Nxd4 Bc5 18. Nxe4 Bxd4 (18... dxe4 19. Ne6 e3 20. f3 Qd5 21. Nxc5 bxc5 22. Qe4 $18) 19. Bg5 Qc8 20. Rad1 dxe4 21. Rxd4 Qf5 22. Be7 Rf7 23. Bd7 Qg6 24. Qxc7 e3 25. fxe3 Bf3 26. Be6 {1-0 Greenfeld,A-Almasi,Z/Mainz 2004}) (16... Na5 17. b4 Nc4 18. Nxc4 dxc4 19. Rxe4 Qd5 20. Bxc4 Qxe4 21. Qxe4 Bxe4 22. Ne5 Bf6 23. Be3 $11) 17. Nxe4 dxe4 18. Qxe4 Nxd4 19. Qxd4 Bxf3 20. Qxd6 Bxd6 21. Bd2 $11) 15... Ng4 (15... a5 16. Ng5 $1 Nxd4 (16... Qd6 17. Ndf3 $16) 17. Nxh7 Bc5 $1 (17... Ba6 18. Nxf8 Bxd3 19. Ne6 Nxe6 20. Rxe6 $16) 18. Nxf8 Qxf8 19. Nf3 $1 (19. Nf1 Bc8 $1 20. Ne3 a4 $1 $44) 19... Ng4 (19... Nxf3+ 20. Qxf3 Ne4 21. Bxe4 dxe4 22. Qxf8+ Rxf8 23. Be3 $18) 20. Bf4 Ne6 $5 (20... Nxf3+ 21. Qxf3 Bxf2+ 22. Kg2 Bxe1 23. Qxg4 $18) 21. Ne5 $1 (21. Nh4 Bxf2+ 22. Kf1 $18 {Tkachiev,V-Sulskis,S/Istanbul 2003}) 21... Bxf2+ 22. Kf1 Nxh2+ 23. Kxf2 Nxf4 24. Kg1 Qc5+ 25. Kh1 Nxd3 26. Nxd3 $18) 16. h3 Nh6 17. b4 Nf5 $5 (17... Bf6 18. Nb3 Qd7 19. Qc2 Qxh3 20. Bxh6 gxh6 (20... Qxh6 21. Kg2 $18) 21. b5 $16 {Laznicka,V-Polak,T/Czech Rep. 2006}) 18. Bb2 a6 19. Rc1 $14 {.}) 8. Qc2 c5 ({White keeps a slight advantage also with the other options: a)} 8... Bb4 9. Bd3 c5 (9... O-O 10. O-O Bxd2 11. Bxd2 d5 12. cxd5 exd5 13. e5 Ne4 14. Bxa5 bxa5 15. Nd2 $16 {Tancik,K-Mirkovic,S/Vrnjacka Banja 2006}) 10. dxc5 (10. a3 $5 Bxd2+ 11. Bxd2 b5 $1 12. b3 cxd4 13. Nxd4 bxc4 14. bxc4 Nc6 15. Nxc6 Bxc6 16. O-O $14) 10... Bxc5 11. O-O Rc8 12. Qd1 Ng4 13. a3 Qf6 14. Rb1 Nc6 15. b4 Bd6 16. Bb2 $14 {Barlov,D-Benjamin,J/New York 1987.}) ({b)} 8... d5 9. cxd5 exd5 10. e5 Ne4 11. Bb5+ c6 12. Bd3 f5 13. exf6 Qxf6 14. O-O Nxd2 15. Nxd2 O-O-O (15... Qxd4 $2 16. Nf3 Qc5 17. Re1+ Be7 18. b4 $1 $18) 16. Bf5+ Kb8 17. Nf3 h6 18. Ne5 $14 {Sargissian,G-Shetty,R/Dubai 2005.}) 9. e5 ({White could instead play} 9. d5 $5 {, with a slightly better and secure position:} exd5 10. exd5 Bd6 11. Bd3 $14 {.}) 9... Ng4 10. h3 Nh6 11. Ne4 Bxe4 $2 ({Black had to play} 11... Nf5 $1 12. Bg5 Qb8 (12... Be7 13. Bxe7 Qxe7 14. dxc5 bxc5 15. g4 $1 Nd4 16. Nxd4 cxd4 17. O-O-O O-O 18. f4 $14) 13. dxc5 Bxc5 14. O-O-O Bxf2 15. Qxf2 Bxe4 16. g4 $44) ({but not} 11... f5 $6 12. exf6 gxf6 13. Bxh6 Bxh6 14. Nd6+ Ke7 15. Nxb7 Nxb7 16. Bg2 $16 {.}) 12. Qxe4 cxd4 13. Bxh6 gxh6 14. O-O-O Rc8 15. Kb1 $3 ({A very strong move, after which Black cannot continue with 15...xc4 16.xd4 b5 (16...a5 17.b5 and ad1, with powerful pressure on the backward d7-pawn) 17.xc4 bxc4 18.xc4 +/-. The immediate} 15. Rxd4 $6 Bc5 $1 16. Rd2 b5 $1 {would give Black plenty of hope.}) 15... Bg7 $6 ({White retains his advantage after} 15... Nc6 $1 16. Nxd4 Nxd4 17. Rxd4 Bc5 18. Rd2 Qc7 {thanks to the backward d7-pawn and the weakened black king, but this line had to be preferred anyway.}) 16. Nxd4 $1 f5 17. Qe3 $1 Qe7 ({Naturally,} 17... Nxc4 $2 18. Bxc4 Rxc4 19. Nxe6 $1 {would be disastrous for Black.}) 18. Nb5 $1 O-O 19. Nd6 Rc7 {White has an excellent position, having fixed the backward black d-pawn with both knight and pawn. Moreover, White's overall pawn structure is superior and he has a significant space advantage. As a result of the above, his position is almost winning. The only thing White must cater for is possible counterplay by means of 20...f4!? 21.gxf4 h4.} 20. f4 $1 {Not only stopping the aforementioned counterplay but also preparing h2-d2!, increasing the pressure on the backward d-pawn. The f1-bishop will be developed later, wherever and whenever it will be necessary.} Nb7 {Threatening 21...xd6! 22.exd6? f6!.} 21. Rh2 $1 Qd8 ({Black is hardly in an enviable position, but could at least prolong the game with} 21... Nc5 {.}) 22. Nb5 $1 Rc5 23. Qf3 $1 {And at the same time Black resigned, in view of} Rxb5 ({No relief was offered by} 23... Na5 24. b4) ({or} 23... Qb8 24. Rxd7 Rf7 25. Rxf7 Kxf7 26. Qxb7+ $1 {.}) 24. Qxb7 $1 Rc5 25. Rxd7 {.} 1-0


