1. d4 Nf6 2. Nf3 g6 3. c4 Bg7 4. g3 O-O 5. Bg2 d6 6. O-O Nc6 7. d5 Na5 8. Nbd2 {(D) } b5 $5 (8... c5 {is the main line here, but I really believe in this move.}) 9. cxb5 ({A normal follow-up. Alternatives are: a)} 9. Qc2 bxc4 (9... Nxc4 10. Nxc4 Bf5 11. Qb3 bxc4 12. Qxc4 e6) 10. Nxc4 Bf5 11. Qa4 Nxc4 12. Qxc4 e6 $11) ({b)} 9. Nd4 $5 Nxc4 (9... bxc4 10. b4 (10. Qa4 c5 11. dxc6 Qb6 12. N2f3 (12. e3 Rb8 $15) 12... Ne4 $15 { c5}) 10... cxb3 (10... Ng4 11. Bb2 (11. N2f3 c5 12. dxc6 e5 13. bxa5 exd4 14. Nxd4 Qxa5 15. c7 d5 $13) 11... Rb8 {b1)} 12. a3 ({b2)} 12. Bc3 Bxd4 13. Bxd4 Rxb4 14. Bc3 Rb5 (14... c5 15. dxc6 $16) 15. a4 Rc5 16. Bb4 Nf6 {Black sacrifices the exchange for some pawns and a good game.} 17. Bxc5 dxc5 18. e4 c6 $44) ({b3)} 12. Qa4 c5 13. dxc6 Qb6 14. c7 Qxc7 15. Bc3 e5 16. Nc2 Nb7 $13 (16... Nb3 $2 17. axb3 cxb3 18. Qxb3 Be6 19. Qb2 Rfc8 20. Ra3 d5 21. e3 $18)) 12... e5 (12... c5 13. dxc6 e5 14. N4f3 (14. Nc2 d5 $132) 14... Nxc6 15. h3 (15. Nxc4 $6 d5 $17) 15... c3 16. Bxc3 Nh6 17. Nc4 Nf5 18. Rc1 $14) 13. N4f3 (13. dxe6 c5) 13... Nb3 14. Nxb3 cxb3 15. h3 Nh6 16. Qxb3 f5 17. Rac1 $14) 11. axb3 Nb7 12. Nc6 Qe8 13. Bb2 a6 (13... e6 14. e4 Bd7 15. Qf3 e5 16. Qc3 $44) 14. Qc2 e6 15. e4 $44) 10. Nxb5 (10. Nxc4 bxc4 11. Qa4 c5 12. dxc6 d5) 10... Nb6 (10... Nxd2 11. Bxd2 $14) 11. Nc3 Rb8 $13) 9... Nxd5 {(D) } 10. Rb1 {Probably the best. Options are} ({a)} 10. Qa4 $6 Nb7 11. Qh4 (11. Nd4 Nb6 12. Qb4 a6 13. Nc6 Qe8 14. Na5 Qxb5 15. Qxb5 axb5 16. Nxb7 Ra7 17. Nxd6 cxd6 $17) (11. Qc2 a6 12. Nd4 Bxd4 13. Bxd5 axb5 14. Qe4 c6 15. Bxc6 Qb6 16. Nb3 Ra4 17. Nxd4 Rxd4 $13 {Ujtelky,M-Stulik,V/Prague 1955}) 11... e6 12. Qxd8 (12. Rd1 Qxh4 13. Nxh4 Bd7 $15) 12... Rxd8 (12... Nxd8 13. e4 Nb4) 13. Nb3 a6 $15 {Minasian,A-Ivanchuk,V/Montecatini Terme 2000 or}) ({b)} 10. Nb3 {which allows Black to exchange his badly placed knight, cannot be satisfactory for White:} Nxb3 11. Qxb3 Bb7 (11... Nb6 12. Rd1 Bb7 13. Bg5 c5 14. a4 a5 15. Rac1 (15. bxa6 Bxa6 16. Bxe7 Qxe7 17. Qxb6 Bxe2 18. Qxd6 Qxd6 19. Rxd6 Bxb2 20. Ra2 Rfd8 $13) 15... c4 16. Qa3 h6 17. Be3 d5 18. b3 Rc8 19. Bc5 Rxc5 20. Qxc5 cxb3 $44 {Bunzmann,D-Enzmann,S/Halle 1996}) 12. Nd2 e6 13. Nc4 Rb8 14. Rd1 a6 15. e4 Nf6 16. e5 Nd5 17. exd6 axb5 18. dxc7 Qxc7 $11 {Cserna,L-Adorjan,A/Hungary 1975}) 10... c5 ({a)} 10... Rb8 11. e4 Nb4 (11... Nb6 12. b4 Nac4 13. Nxc4 Nxc4 14. Nd4 $14) 12. a3 Na2 13. Qc2 $1 Rxb5 14. b4 Nc3 15. bxa5 Nxb1 16. Nxb1 $13 {Kochyev,A-Kupreichik,V/Moscow 1989}) ({b)} 10... a6 11. e4 Nb6 12. b4 Nac4 13. Nxc4 Nxc4 14. bxa6 Bxa6 15. a4 c5 $1 $13) ({c)} 10... Bd7 11. e4 Nb4 12. Nb3 c5 13. Nxa5 Qxa5 14. a3 Na2 15. Bg5 Rfe8 16. e5 Bxb5 (16... Qxb5 17. exd6 exd6 18. Qxd6 Rac8 $13) 17. Qb3 Bxf1 18. Bxf1 Nb4 19. axb4 Qxb4 $13 {Loebler,H-Sinowjew,J/Austria 1994}) 11. bxc6 Nxc6 12. Nb3 Nb6 13. Nfd4 Nxd4 14. Nxd4 d5 15. a4 Qd7 $1 ({Although} 15... a5 {is not bad either:} 16. b3 (16. Nc6 Qc7 17. Bxd5 Nxd5 18. Qxd5 Bb7 $19) 16... e6 17. Ba3 Re8 18. Nb5 $13) ({Black should avoid} 15... e5 16. Nc6 Qc7 17. Nb4 $1 (17. a5 Qxc6 18. axb6 Be6 19. bxa7 Rxa7 $15) 17... Be6 18. a5 Qd6 19. axb6 Qxb4 20. bxa7 Rxa7 21. Bxd5 Rd8 22. Bd2 Qe7 23. Bxe6 Qxe6 24. Qc2 $14) 16. b3 e5 $6 ({Too early! With} 16... Rb8 $1 17. Bb2 e5 18. a5 Na8 19. Nc2 Nc7 {Black would secure a slight advantage.}) 17. Nc2 Rb8 ({The alternative was} 17... Bb7 18. a5 Nc8 19. a6 (19. Nb4 d4) 19... Bxa6 20. Nb4 Bb7 21. Nxd5 $13 {and Black should seriously consider it.}) 18. a5 Na4 $2 ({A blunder. The only move was} 18... Nc4 19. Qxd5 Qxd5 20. Bxd5 Nxa5 21. Ba3 Rd8 22. Rfd1 Bb7 $11) 19. Bd2 Nc5 20. Bb4 Rb5 21. Qxd5 Qxd5 22. Bxd5 Bf5 23. Bc4 $1 ({Precise, as} 23. e4 $2 Bxe4 24. Bxe4 Nxe4 25. Bxf8 Bxf8 {would give Black some compensation.}) 23... Rxb4 ({Also unattractive was} 23... Rfb8 24. Bxb5 Rxb5 25. Rb2 e4 (25... Bxc2 26. Rxc2 Rxb4 27. Rxc5 $18) 26. Rbb1 e3 27. Bxc5 Rxc5 28. Nxe3 Bxb1 29. Rxb1 $16) 24. Nxb4 Bxb1 25. Rxb1 Rb8 (25... Rc8 26. Nd5 Kf8 27. b4 $16) 26. Nc6 Rb7 27. Rd1 Bf6 28. b4 Na4 (28... Ne6 29. Rd6 Kg7 30. Bxe6 fxe6 31. e4 $18) 29. Rd6 Kg7 30. e4 $1 Nc3 31. f3 Rc7 (31... Be7 32. Nxe7 Rxe7 33. Rc6 $18) 32. Bd3 Na2 33. b5 Nc3 34. b6 axb6 35. axb6 Rb7 36. Na5 Rb8 37. b7 Na4 38. Rc6 1-0


