1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 g6 3. Nc3 d5 4. Nf3 Bg7 5. cxd5 Nxd5 6. e4 Nxc3 7. bxc3 c5 8. Bb5+ Nc6 9. O-O cxd4 10. cxd4 O-O 11. Be3 Bg4 12. Bxc6 bxc6 13. Rc1 Qa5 14. Qd2 Qxd2 ({It looks better for Black to exchange the queens directly, as then he can have some activity on the queenside with his remaining pieces. Alternatives are: a)} 14... Qa4 15. Rc5 (15. Qc2 Qxc2 16. Rxc2 Bxf3 17. gxf3 f5 $1 $13 (17... Rfd8 $6 18. e5 $14 {Grigorchuk,S-Fratini,M Heraklion 2008})) 15... Bxf3 16. gxf3 Rfd8 17. Ra5 Qc4 18. Rc1 Qe6 19. Kg2 $14 {Gasthofer,V-Neubauer,M Germany 2010.}) ({b)} 14... Qa6 15. Rc5 (15. Ne5 Bxe5 16. dxe5 Rfd8 17. Qb4 Rd7 18. h3 Be6 19. Rfd1 Rb7 20. Qc3 $14 {Ferozkohi,I-Illingworth,M North Geelong 2011}) 15... Bxf3 (15... Rfd8 16. Rfc1 Rac8 17. Ne5 Bxe5 18. Rxe5 Be6 19. Ra5 Qb7 20. Qc3 f6 21. Qc5 $16 {Martinez Garcia,J-Ripari,M Buenos Aires 2003}) 16. gxf3 Rfd8 17. Rfc1 $14 {.}) 15. Nxd2 Rfd8 16. e5 $5 {The most decent try, protecting the white centre and preparing to pressure the weak black c-pawn. Black must be on the alert.} Be6 ({Black has a wide choice here: a)} 16... Rac8 17. Nb3 $1 Be6 18. Na5 Bd5 (18... Bxa2 $2 19. Nxc6 $18) 19. Rc2 $14 {[%csl Gc6][%cal Gf1c1] .}) ({b)} 16... Rdc8 17. Nb3 (17. Ne4 Be6 18. Rc2 Bd5 19. f3 f6 $11) 17... Rab8 (17... a5 18. Rc5 a4 19. Na5 $16) 18. Rc5 (18. Na5 Bd7 19. Rc5 Rb5 20. Rfc1 f6 $1 $11) 18... Rb5 19. Rfc1 Bd7 20. R5c4 $14 {.}) ({c)} 16... Bd7 17. Nb3 Rab8 18. Rfe1 $1 (18. Rc5 Rb5 19. Rfc1 f6 20. exf6 Bxf6 21. R5c4 Be6 $11) (18. Rc2 f6 $132) 18... Rb5 (18... f6 19. e6 Be8 20. Rc4 $14) 19. Nc5 Bf5 20. f3 $14 {.}) ({d)} 16... f6 $5 17. exf6 Bxf6 (17... exf6 $2 18. Rxc6 $16) 18. f3 (18. Rxc6 Bxd4 19. Bxd4 Rxd4 20. Nb3 Ra4 21. h3 Rc8 22. Rxc8+ Bxc8 23. Rc1 Ba6 $11) 18... Bf5 19. Rfe1 $1 (19. Rxc6 Bxd4 20. Bxd4 Rxd4 21. Nb3 Ra4 22. g4 Rc8 (22... Bd3 23. Rf2 $14) 23. Rxc8+ Bxc8 24. Rc1 Be6 25. Nc5 Rc4 26. Rxc4 Bxc4 27. a3 Kf7 28. f4 Kf6 29. Kf2 Bd5 30. Nd7+ (30. Ke3 h5 $11) 30... Kf7 31. Ke3 h5 32. gxh5 gxh5 33. f5 e6 $11) 19... Rab8 (19... Bxd4 20. Bxd4 Rxd4 21. Nb3 $14) 20. Nb3 (20. Rxc6 Rb2 $132) 20... Bd7 21. Bf4 Rb5 22. Be5 $14 {.}) 17. Rxc6 Bxa2 18. Ra1 (18. Rc7 {is less accurate:} a5 19. Ra1) 18... Be6 (18... Bd5 $5 {should be examined seriously:} {c)} 19. Rc5 ({a)} 19. Rca6 Rd7 20. f3 f6 21. f4 (21. e6 Rb7 22. Ne4 f5 23. Nc5 Rb2 $15) 21... e6 {½-½ Skembris,S-Stohl,I Vrnjacka Banja 1989.}) ({b)} 19. Rc7 $1 a5 (19... Rdc8 20. Rxc8+ Rxc8 21. Ra5 (21. Rxa7 $14) 21... e6 (21... Rc1+ $2 22. Nf1 $18) 22. f3 Rc7 23. Ne4 $14) 20. Ra4 (20. Nc4 Rdb8 21. Rc5 (21. Nxa5 Rb5 22. Bd2 Rb2 23. Bc1 Rb5 24. Bd2 $11) 21... e6 22. Rcxa5 Rxa5 23. Nxa5 Rb5 24. h3 f6 25. Nc4 {½-½ Kabanov,N-Sergienko,S Nizhnij Novgorod 1999.}) 20... f6 (20... e6 21. Rc5 $14) 21. f4 e6 22. Rc5 $14 {.}) 19... Bf8 (19... e6 20. Nc4 Rdb8 21. f3) 20. f3 f5 21. Ra6 (21. exf6 exf6 22. Rca5 Rd7 23. Ne4 Bxe4 24. fxe4 $11 {Pribyl,M-Oral,T Turnov 1996.})) 19. Rca6 Rd7 20. Ne4 (20. f3 $5 Rc7) 20... Rc7 (20... Bd5 21. Nc3 (21. f3 $1 Rb7 22. h4 h6 23. Kh2 $14) 21... Bc4 22. R6a4 (22. Rc6 $14) 22... Rc7 23. Rc1 Rac8 24. Ne4 Bf8 25. Ra5) (20... Bc4 21. R6a5 f6 22. f4 $14 {.}) 21. R6a5 (21. f3 $14 {.}) 21... Bc4 22. f3 (22. Rc1 $1 Rac8 23. Nc5 (23. f4 f6 24. Nc5 Bd5 25. Rca1 e6 26. Rxa7 fxe5 27. fxe5 Bf8 28. Nd7 Be7 29. Nb6 Rxa7 30. Rxa7 Rc3 31. Nxd5 exd5 32. Bh6 Ba3 33. e6 {1-0 Tsorbatzoglou,T-Tsevremes,I Kavala 1991}) 23... Bd5 24. Rca1 $14 {.}) 22... f6 23. f4 (23. exf6 Bxf6 (23... exf6 24. Rc1 Rd8 25. Nd2 Rdc8 26. Rxc4 Rxc4 27. Nxc4 Rxc4 28. Rxa7 f5 29. Rd7 f4 30. Bxf4 Bxd4+ 31. Kf1 $14) 24. Nxf6+ exf6 25. Rc1 a6 26. d5 Rcc8 27. Kf2 Bb5 28. Bc5 Kf7 $11 {.}) 23... h6 24. h3 Kh7 25. Rc1 Rac8 26. d5 $6 ({Leads to nowhere. White should have opted for} 26. exf6 Bxf6 27. Nxf6+ exf6 28. d5 a6 29. d6 Rd7 30. f5 $14 {.}) 26... fxe5 27. d6 exd6 28. Nxd6 exf4 $1 29. Bxf4 Bd4+ 30. Kh2 Rf8 $1 31. Bg3 $2 ({In time-trouble White over-estimates his chances. Correct was} 31. Be5 Bxe5+ 32. Rxe5 Rf4 33. Ra5 Kg8 34. Rxc4 Rcxc4 35. Nxc4 Rxc4 36. Rxa7 $11 {.}) 31... Bb6 $2 ({In mutual time-trouble Black blunders, missing the strong} 31... Rf1 $1 32. Rxf1 Bxf1 $17 {.}) 32. Ra4 $2 ({Another blunder in quick succession. With} 32. Raa1 $1 Rfc8 33. Nxc8 Rxc8 34. Rc2 Be6 35. Rxc8 Bxc8 36. Bb8 $18 {White should have won.}) 32... Rf1 $1 {Now it's a draw!} 33. Rcxc4 Bg1+ 1/2-1/2


