1. e4 e6 2. d4 d5 3. Nc3 Nf6 4. Bg5 Be7 5. e5 Nfd7 6. h4 Bxg5 7. hxg5 Qxg5 8. Qd3 (8. Nf3 Qe7 9. Qd2 Nb6 $13 (9... Nc6 10. Nb5 Nb6 11. c3 a6 12. Na3 Bd7 $11 {Lehner,O-Sutovsky,E/Feugen 2006} 13. Nc2 $2 O-O-O 14. Bd3 h6) 10. g4 $2 Bd7 11. Bd3 Nc6 12. O-O-O O-O-O $16 {Khakhanov,V-Kopylov,A/Salekhard 2006} {b)} 13. Kb1 Kb8 14. Rh5 Nb4) (8. Rh5 Qe7 $17 {Orekhov,N-Kopylov,A/Salekhard 2006} 9. Qg4 f5 10. Qh3 Nf8 11. O-O-O Bd7 12. g4 fxg4 13. Qxg4 Nc6 14. Rg5 Rg8 15. Nge2) 8... h5 (8... g6 9. Nf3 Qe7 10. Qe3 Nc6 11. O-O-O $11 Nb6 $1 $15 {There do exist some alternative, not very often played lines: a)} 12. Ng5 (12. Rh6 Bd7 13. Qg5 Qxg5+ 14. Nxg5 Ke7 15. Nxh7 $14 {Volodin,A-Savickas,A/Tallin 2006} Rac8 16. f4 $1) 12... Bd7 13. Nxh7 O-O-O 14. Be2 Be8 15. a3 Kb8 $11 16. Bb5 $6) 9. Nf3 Qe7 10. g4 g6 (10... h4 11. O-O-O Nb6 (11... g5 12. Qe3 Rg8 $17 13. Nd2 $1 Nb6 14. f4 gxf4 15. Qxf4 Nc6 $11 16. Nf3) 12. Qe3 $17 {Not of a help was} Nc6 13. g5 {but White had to try} Bd7 14. Nxh4 $17 {More dangerous for White is} O-O-O $1 15. f4) 11. gxh5 gxh5 (11... Rxh5 {would be won for Black. The significance of the white king's misplacement is evident in this line.} {A serious mistake.} 12. Rxh5 {is fine.} {Dangerous, as it will help Black obtain active play. Waiting with} gxh5 {is more normal.} 13. Qh7 $1 {is simply winning a pawn!}) 12. Qe3 Nb6 13. O-O-O Bd7 14. Be2 Nc6 15. Qf4 O-O-O 16. Rdg1 Rdf8 17. Rg7 Be8 18. a3 Nd8 19. Rhg1 h4 (19... c5) 20. Rh1 c5 21. dxc5 Qxc5 22. Nd4 Nc4 23. Rg4 (23. Bxc4 Qxc4 24. Nce2 (24. Rxh4 $1 {and} Rxh4 25. Qxh4 $1 Nc6 26. Ncb5 {are even worse.} {Compulsory, as} Qf1+ 27. Kd2 Nxe5 28. Qe7 $1 Qxf2+ 29. Kc3 Qe3+ 30. Kb4) 24... Nc6 25. Rg4 h3 26. Rg3 h2 27. Rg2 Nxd4 $1 {would have won quickly.} {White has no other useful move. Both} 28. Nxd4) 23... Nc6 (23... Nxa3 24. Rgxh4 (24. Nb3 Qc7 25. Qb4 (25. Qe3 Nc4 26. Bxc4 ({Incomprehensible. Black lost a valuable tempo, allowing White to survive.} 26. Qxa7 $1 Nxe5 27. Rgxh4 Rxh4 28. Rxh4 {really wasn't that hard!} {This doesn't spoil things, but} Rg8 $1) 26... dxc4 27. Nd2 b5 {½-½ (71) Vul,A (2454)-Grivas,E (2528) Athens 1999 CBM 122 [Grivas,Efstratios]}) 25... Nc4 26. Bxc4 Nc6 27. Qc5 Nxe5 28. Qxc7+ Kxc7) 24... Rxh4 25. Rxh4 Rg8 26. Nb3 $2 Qc7 27. Kd2 Nc4+ 28. Bxc4 dxc4 29. Qxc4) 24. Nb3 Qb6 (24... Qe7 25. Bxc4 dxc4 26. Nd2) 25. Bxc4 dxc4 26. Nd2 h3 27. Nxc4 Qc7 28. Rg3 h2 (28... f6 29. Nb5 Qe7 30. Rgxh3 (30. Nbd6+ Kb8 31. Rgxh3 Rxh3 32. Rxh3 fxe5 33. Qg3) 30... Rxh3 31. Rxh3 fxe5 32. Qe3) 29. Nb5 Qe7 30. Rb3 Rh4 (30... Qh4 31. Nbd6+ (31. Qe3) 31... Kb8 32. Rxb7+ Ka8 33. Qe3 (33. Qxh4 Rxh4 34. Rc7 Rg8 35. Rxh2 Rxh2 36. Rc8+ Nb8 37. Nxe8) 33... Nd4 (33... Rfg8 34. Qxa7+ Nxa7 35. Nb6#) 34. Rxh2 Qxh2 35. Qxd4) 31. Nbd6+ Kb8 32. Rxb7+ Ka8 33. Rxe7 Rxf4 34. Rc7 Rh4 35. Rc8+ Nb8 36. Nxe8 1/2-1/2


