 33. Kf1) 31. Qd3 Qh5 32. fxg4 Qxg4+ 33. Kf1 f3) 29. exf6 Bxf6 30. Bb4 Bd3 31. Bd6+ Ka8 32. Rxc4 {[White's advantage in this endgame is obvious, although he managed to misplace it!]} Rxc4 (32... dxc4) 33. Be5 Bxe5 34. dxe5 Kb8 35. Rd1 Qb6+ (35... Bxe2 $2 36. Qxe2 Qb6+ 37. Kf1 $2 Qe6 $16 38. a5) 36. Kh1 Bxe2 37. Qxe2 Qe3 38. Qb2 d4 39. Qa2 Rc1 40. Qg8+ Kc7 41. b6+ (41. Qg7+ Kb6 42. Qf6+ Ka5 43. Qd8+ b6 44. Qxd4 Qxd4) 41... axb6 1/2-1/2


