1. d4 d5 2. c4 Bf5 3. cxd5 Bxb1 4. Qa4+ c6 (4... Qd7 5. Qxd7+ Nxd7 6. Rxb1 Ngf6 7. Nf3 Nb6 8. e3 Nbxd5 9. Be2 e6 10. O-O) 5. dxc6 Nxc6 6. Rxb1 Qxd4 (6... e5 7. Bd2 exd4 (7... Qxd4 8. Qxd4 Nxd4 9. Nf3 Nc6 10. e4 Nf6 11. Bb5 Nxe4 12. Bxc6+ bxc6 13. Nxe5 Bc5) 8. g3 Bc5 9. Bg2 Nge7 10. Nh3 O-O 11. O-O Re8 12. Nf4 Bb6 13. Rbc1 Rc8 14. Rc2 (14. Rfe1 Ng6 15. Nd5) 14... Ng6 15. Rfc1 Nxf4 16. Bxf4 h6) 7. Qxd4 Nxd4 8. e3 (8. Nf3 Nc2+ 9. Kd1 Nb4 10. Bd2 e6 11. e3 a6) 8... Nc6 9. Bb5 Rc8 10. Bd2 (10. Nf3 e6) 10... e6 (10... a6 11. Ba4 b5 12. Bd1 e6 13. Rc1 Bd6 14. Bf3 Kd7 15. Ke2 Nf6) 11. Rc1 Bd6 (11... Nge7 12. Nf3 a6 13. Ba4 b5 14. Bc2 Nd5 15. Be4) (11... a6 12. Bxc6+ Rxc6 13. Rxc6 bxc6 14. Nf3 Bd6 15. Ke2 Nf6 16. Rc1) 12. Bxc6+ Rxc6 13. Rxc6 bxc6 14. Nf3 Ne7 15. Ke2 (15. e4) 15... O-O (15... Kd7 $16 {.} 16. Bc3 (16. Rd1) 16... f6 $14 {.} 17. e4 Ng6 18. Rd1 Ke7 $16 {.} 19. g3) (15... Nd5 16. Rc1 Kd7 17. Rc4 (17. Ng5) 17... Rb8 18. b3) 16. Rc1 Rb8 17. b3 $14 {White can create a kingside initiative. On the other hand Black is quite slow on the other side of the board.} Kf8 18. Rc4 h6 (18... Ke8 $14 {.} 19. Rg4 g6 20. Ng5 h5 21. Ra4 Nc8 22. h3) 19. Bc3 Rb5 $6 20. e4 Rc5 (20... g5 21. h3 h5 $18 {.} 22. Bf6 g4 23. hxg4 hxg4 24. Nd4) (20... Rb6) (20... g6) 21. e5 Rxc4 (21... Nd5 22. exd6 Nxc3+ $16 {.} {In a tactical position both players failed to act properly. White could win once more with} 23. Kd3 $1 Rxc4 24. Kxc4 Nxa2 25. Ne5 $18 {.}) (21... Nd5 22. Bd2 Be7 23. Ra4 $16 {.}) 22. exd6 Rc5 (22... Rxc3 23. d7 Rc2+ 24. Nd2 (24. Kd1)) (22... Nd5 $18 {.} 23. Bxg7+ Kxg7 24. bxc4 (24. d7 $1 $18 Nf4+ 25. Kd2 $1 Rc5)) 23. Bxg7+ Ke8 (23... Kxg7 24. dxe7) 24. dxe7 Kxe7 (24... Rc2+ 25. Nd2 Rxa2 26. Bf6 {.}) 25. Bxh6 $1 Rc2+ 26. Bd2 Rxa2 $2 27. h4 $2 Rb2 (27... c5 28. Kd3 Rb2 29. Kc3) 28. b4 c5 $6 29. bxc5 $6 a5 30. Ne5 $1 {An excellent tactical idea and probably the only move to keep White's advantage alive.} a4 $6 31. Nc4 $1 Rb3 32. c6 e5 (32... Kd8 33. Ba5+ Kc8 34. Nd6+) 33. Ba5 $18 Rb5 34. c7 Kd7 (34... Rc5 35. Bb4) 35. c8=Q+ 1-0


