1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 Bc5 4. c3 Nf6 5. d4 exd4 6. cxd4 Bb4+ 7. Nc3 (7. Bd2 Bxd2+ (7... Nxe4 $14 {½-½ Cebalo, M-Braga,F/Reggio Emilia 1991} 8. Bxb4 Nxb4) 8. Nbxd2 a6 $16 {Komarov,D-Delanoy,A/Le Touquet 1993.} 9. Ba4 b5 10. Bb3 d5 11. e5 Nh5 (11... Ne4) 12. O-O $44 {Kuijf,M-Brenninkmeijer,J/Netherlands 1992} {But by choosing the 'obvious' d)} Nf4 {alternative, Black can fight:} 13. a3 Be6 14. Bc2 O-O 15. Nb3 Bg4 16. Rc1 Qc8 17. Bxh7+ Kh8 {and it transposes to Grivas,E-Gelashvili,T/Kocaeli 2008.} 18. Rxc6 Bh3 19. gxh3 Qxh3 $14 {Cvitan,O-Braga,F/Reggio Emilia 1991} 20. Ne1 $5 Qxh7 21. Qg4 g5 22. Nc5) (7. Kf1 d5 8. e5 Nd7 9. Qb3 Rb8 $16 {Cvitan,O-Soffer,R/Biel 1990} 10. a3 $2 Be7 11. Qxd5 O-O 12. Qe4 Nb6 13. Bd3 g6 $16 14. Bh6 Re8 15. Nc3 Bf5 16. Qe3 Nxd4 17. Nxd4 Bxd3+ 18. Qxd3 c5 19. Rd1 cxd4 20. Qxd4 Qxd4 21. Rxd4 Rbc8 $14 22. Ne4 $6 Rc2 23. g3 Rxb2 $16 24. Kg2 Rb5 25. Nd6 Bxd6 $14 26. exd6 Rh5 27. Be3 Nd7 28. Rc1) 7... Nxe4 8. O-O (8. Bd2 Nxd2 9. Qxd2 Qe7+ $44 {Calderin,R-Pazos,P/Cienfuegos 1991} {I do not think that the text move helps Black; nor do the following alternatives: a)} 10. Be2 $6 Bxc3 11. bxc3 O-O 12. O-O d6 13. Bd3 Bg4 14. Ng5 h6 15. Ne4 Rfe8 16. Rfe1 Qd7 17. Re3 Kh8 18. Rg3 f5 $16 {Vallejo Pons,F-Aronian,L/Khanty Mansiysk 2005.} {b)} 19. Nf6 $6 gxf6 20. Qxh6+ $2 Qh7 {1-0 Banikas,H-Kalaitzoglou,P/Kallithea 2008.} 21. Qxf6+ Qg7 $16 {c)} 22. Qh4+ $6 Qh7 23. Qxh7+ Kxh7 24. Rxg4 Rf8 $1) 8... Bxc3 $6 (8... Nxc3 9. bxc3 Be7 10. d5 Nb8 11. d6 cxd6 12. h4 Nc6 13. Re1 $16 {Magerramov,E-Goldin,V/Moscow 1991.} O-O $2 14. Bg5 $18 {.} {A strong retreat as White has not played e3 yet.} Ne5 {is not great:} 15. Bxe7 Qxe7 16. Ng5 Qf6 17. Qd4 Qg6 18. Re3 a6 19. Be2 b5 20. Rg3 $1 Bb7 21. Bd3 Nxd3 22. Ne6 $11 {Navara,D-Carlsen,M/Wijk aan Zee 2006.} Qxg3 $6 23. fxg3 fxe6 24. Qxd3 Bd5 25. a4 bxa4 26. Rxa4 a5 27. Ra1 Rfb8 28. c4 $44 {Donoso,C-Endara,N/Pichincha 1962} Bc6 29. Qd2 a4) 9. d5 $1 (9. bxc3 O-O 10. d5 Nxc3 11. Qd3 Nxb5 12. Qxb5 Ne7 13. d6 Ng6 (13... cxd6 14. Ba3 b6 (14... Ng6 15. Rfe1 $18 {Goldstern,F-Ruefenacht,M/Switzerland 1993.} (15. Bxd6 Re8) 15... b6 16. Bxd6 Re8 17. Rxe8+ $18 {Better than} Qxe8 18. Re1 Qd8 19. Qd5 Ba6 20. Ng5 Bc4 $14 {Arsovic,G-Ivanovic,B/Herceg Novi 2007.} 21. Qxc4 Qxg5 22. Qe4 Qd8) 15. Bxd6 Bb7 16. Rae1 Re8) 14. Bg5 c6 15. Qc4 Qa5 16. Rfe1 b6 17. h4 Ba6 18. Qg4 f5 19. Qd4 h6 20. h5 hxg5 21. hxg6 Rf6 22. Re5 Qa3 $18 {.} {Exchanging pieces when a pawn down cannot be the right policy for Black. he had to play} 23. Rd1 Raf8 24. Re7 Qc5 $16 {.} 25. Qxc5 bxc5 $16 {.} 26. Ne5 Bc8 27. f3 c4 28. Kf2 c3 29. Rh1 c2 $16 {Lobron,E-Gulko,B/Vienna 1991.} 30. Ke2 c1=Q 31. Rxc1 $16 {Huzman,A-Dizdar,G/Baku 1988} Rxd6) 9... O-O 10. Bd3 Bf6 11. Bxe4 $1 Ne7 12. Qc2 Ng6 13. g4 c6 14. d6 {White has won a precious pawn and Black cannot show any serious compensation.} Qe8 $6 15. Be3 b6 16. Rad1 Ba6 17. Rfe1 Qe6 18. Bf5 Qxa2 19. g5 Bd8 20. Rd4 b5 21. h4 Bb6 22. h5 Bxd4 23. Bxd4 Qd5 24. Be4 Qe6 25. hxg6 Qg4+ 26. Kh2 $18 {The game is theoretically over. White need only 'perform' some basic technique.} fxg6 27. Qb3+ Kh8 28. Ne5 Qh4+ 29. Kg2 Qxg5+ 30. Qg3 Qd2 31. Bc3 Qf4 32. Bc2 b4 33. Qxf4 Rxf4 34. Bd2 Rd4 35. Be3 Rd5 36. Bf4 c5 37. Be4 Rxe5 38. Bxe5 Rb8 39. Bd5 c4 40. Bd4 1-0


