1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 a6 6. Bc4 e6 7. Bb3 {Although other moves have been tried by White instead of the text-move, I believe that this should be his main try.} Nbd7 8. O-O Nc5 9. f4 Qc7 (9... Nfxe4 10. Nxe4 Nxe4 11. f5 $11 {Romanishin,O-Gojak,I/Zadar 1995} e5 12. Qh5 Qe7 (12... d5 13. Bf4 exf4 14. Rae1) 13. Qf3 Nc5 14. Nc6 Qc7 15. Bd5) 10. Qf3 Be7 11. f5 O-O 12. Be3 $14 (12. fxe6 fxe6 13. Nf5 Bd8) 12... Kh8 ({The text-move looks more ambitious than} 12... Bd7 13. fxe6 fxe6 14. Nf5 Bd8 15. Qg3) 13. g4 b5 14. g5 $1 Nfxe4 15. Nxe4 Bb7 16. g6 $2 (16. Nxe6 fxe6 17. g6 Nxe4 18. Qh3 Nf6 19. Bg5 Bd8 $16 {Romanishin,O-Todorcevic,M/Zaragoza 1996}) 16... Bxe4 (16... fxg6 17. Nxc5 dxc5 (17... Bxf3 18. Ncxe6) 18. Nxe6 $14 {was the correct continuation. White felt too optimistic!}) (16... Nxe4 17. Qh3 Nf6 18. Bg5) 17. Nxe6 Bxf3 (17... fxe6 $13 18. Qh5 $2 h6 $18 19. Bxh6) 18. Nxc7 Nxb3 (18... Rac8 19. Bxf7) 19. cxb3 Rac8 $6 20. Rxf3 Rxc7 $4 21. Rh3 $1 {Black loses at least a piece} {The right move at the wrong time!} Bf6 (21... fxg6 22. fxg6 Rf6 23. gxh7) 22. Bf4 Bxb2 $5 23. Re1 (23. Rd1 Be5) 23... Bd4+ 24. Kh1 Be5 25. Bxe5 dxe5 26. Rxe5 $13 {was calling for} (26. Rxe5 $1 Rc1+ 27. Kg2 Rc2+ 28. Kg1 (28. Kf1 fxg6) 28... Rc1+ (28... Rd8 29. Rd3)) 1-0


