1. d4 {Grivas,Efstratios} Nf6 2. Nf3 g6 3. g3 Bg7 4. Bg2 O-O 5. O-O d6 6. c4 Nc6 7. Nc3 Bf5 8. Ne1 Qd7 9. e4 Bh3 {Grivas,Efstratios: '(D) '} 10. Nc2 (10. Nf3 {Grivas,Efstratios} Bxg2 (10... Nh5 11. Be3 Bxg2 12. Kxg2 e6 13. Rc1 a6 14. d5 $13 {Georgiev,K-Nevednichy,V/Sibenik 2006}) 11. Kxg2 e5 12. dxe5 dxe5 13. Qxd7 Nxd7 14. Nd5 Nc5 $11) 10... Bxg2 11. Kxg2 $14 e5 12. d5 Ne7 13. f4 {Grivas,Efstratios: '!?'} (13. f3 $5 {[%cal Yc1e3,Yc4c5]}) (13. b4 {Grivas,Efstratios} a5 14. a3 axb4 15. axb4 Rxa1 16. Nxa1 c6 17. Qd3 cxd5 18. cxd5 Rc8 $11 {Kiseleva,N-Smokina,K/Athens 2005}) 13... exf4 14. Bxf4 (14. gxf4 Nh5 {[%cal Gf7f5]} (14... Rae8 {Grivas,Efstratios} 15. Qf3 Nh5 $5 { f5} 16. f5 Kh8 { g8}) 15. f5 Kh8 $132 {[%cal Ge7g8,Ga8e8]}) 14... Ng4 {[%csl Re5]} 15. Qd2 Kh8 {Grivas,Efstratios: '!' Grivas,Efstratios: ' g8'} 16. Nd4 {[%csl Re7]} Ne5 (16... Ng8 {Grivas,Efstratios} 17. Nf3 Rae8 18. h3 Ne5 19. Nxe5 Bxe5 20. Bxe5+ Rxe5 21. Rf4 { f2, f1}) 17. b3 Ng8 18. Nf3 Nxf3 (18... Rae8 $5) 19. Rxf3 Rae8 20. Re1 a6 ({Good for equality is} 20... Nf6 {Grivas,Efstratios} 21. h3 (21. e5 Nh5 22. exd6 Rxe1 23. Qxe1 Nxf4+ 24. Rxf4 cxd6 $11) 21... Qc8 22. g4 (22. e5 Nh5 23. exd6 Nxf4+ 24. Rxf4 Rxe1 25. Qxe1 cxd6 $11) 22... Nd7 $11) 21. h3 h6 (21... f5 22. Rfe3 $14) (21... Nf6 $6 {Grivas,Efstratios} 22. Bg5) (21... Qc8 $5 {(Grivas,Efstratios)  f6-d7} 22. Bg5 $5 $14) 22. Be3 f5 23. Bd4 fxe4 ({Black could equalize with the simple (and more concrete)} 23... Bxd4 $1 {Grivas,Efstratios} 24. Qxd4+ Qg7 25. Qxg7+ Kxg7 26. Rfe3 fxe4 27. Nxe4 Re5 $11) 24. Rxf8 Rxf8 25. Rxe4 {[%csl Re6]} Kh7 26. Ne2 {[%cal Ye2f4,Yf4e6] Grivas,Efstratios: '!?'} ({Going for the weak e6-square.} 26. Re6 {Grivas,Efstratios} Qf7 27. Re1 Qf3+ 28. Kh2 Rf7 $11) 26... Re8 ({Interesting is} 26... Qf5 $5 {Grivas,Efstratios} 27. Rf4 Qb1 28. Rxf8 Bxf8 29. Nf4 Qe4+ 30. Kh2 Bg7 31. Bxg7 Kxg7 32. Ne6+ Kh7 33. Nxc7 Ne7 $13 {when Black can find good compensation for the lost pawn in his better placed pieces but not}) (26... Nf6 $2 {Grivas,Efstratios} 27. Re6 Nh5 28. Qe3 Rf7 29. Qd3 $18) 27. Rxe8 Qxe8 28. Qd3 (28. Bxg7 {Grivas,Efstratios} Qe4+ 29. Kh2 Kxg7 30. Nf4 Kh7 $11) 28... Qf7 29. Nf4 Bxd4 30. Qxd4 Qf6 {Grivas,Efstratios: '?'} (30... Nf6 31. Ne6 $16) 31. Qxf6 Nxf6 32. Ne6 Ne8 ({Black should not have exchanged queens, as he could have obtained a decent position with 30...e7 31.a7 f5! intending 32...g5, with unclear play. Now however, the knight ending that has arisen is won for White. The e6-knight is immensely superior to the e8-knight, while the black queenside pawns are potential and approachable targets. It must be noted that, instead of the passive 32...e8, the alternative} 32... c6 {Grivas,Efstratios} 33. dxc6 bxc6 34. b4 $1 (34. Nd8 $2 c5 35. Nb7 Ne8 36. Kf3 Kg7 37. Ke4 Nf6+ $1 $11) 34... Kg8 35. Nc7 $1 {was not a help either.}) 33. b4 $1 {[%csl Ra6]} ({It is especially important to immobilize the weak a6-b7 pawn structure. The careless} 33. Kf3 $2 {Grivas,Efstratios} a5 $1 $13 {would give Black serious hope for survival.}) 33... b6 34. Kf3 Kg8 35. a4 Kf7 36. Nd8+ {Grivas,Efstratios: '!'} Ke7 (36... Kf6 {Grivas,Efstratios} 37. Nc6 {intending a5, would also win for White.}) 37. Nc6+ Kd7 38. a5 $1 ({Clearly better than} 38. Nb8+ {Grivas,Efstratios} Kc8 39. Nxa6 $2 Kb7 40. b5 Nf6 {when Black has some survival chances.}) 38... Nf6 (38... bxa5 39. bxa5 $18 {[%cal Yc6b4]}) ({Or} 38... Kc8 {Grivas,Efstratios} 39. Ne7+) 39. b5 $1 axb5 ({Unfortunately,} 39... bxa5 {Grivas,Efstratios} 40. bxa6 Kc8 41. Nxa5 Kb8 42. Nc6+ Ka8 43. Ne7 $1 g5 44. Nc6 {also fails to help Black.}) 40. a6 Kc8 41. Ne7+ Kb8 42. cxb5 $18 g5 43. Ke3 h5 44. Kd4 (44. h4 {Grivas,Efstratios}) 44... h4 45. gxh4 gxh4 46. Ke3 {[%csl Rh4]} 1-0


