1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 g6 3. Nf3 Bg7 4. g3 O-O 5. Bg2 d6 6. O-O Nc6 7. Nc3 Bf5 8. b3 Ne4 9. Bb2 ({The main alternative is} 9. Nd5 {where Black has to withdraw his f5-bishop, obtaining a kind of an excellent Leningrad Dutch set-up:} Bd7 10. Bb2 f5 (10... e6 11. Nf4 Ng5 12. Nxg5 Qxg5 13. e3 Rae8 $11 {Georgiev,K-Nikolaidis,I/Elista OL 1998}) 11. e3 e6 12. Nf4 Qe7 (12... a5 13. a3 Qe7 14. Nd2 Nxd2 15. Qxd2 g5 16. Ne2 e5 $13 {Drasko,M-Greenfeld,A/Belgrade 1994}) 13. Nd3 Rae8 14. b4 Nd8 15. b5 g5 16. a4 Nf7 $13 {Borovikov,V-Maslak,K/Pardubice 2005}) 9... Nxc3 10. Bxc3 Be4 11. Qd2 d5 12. Rfd1 ({The most common continuation. Less satisfactory is} 12. c5 $6 a5 13. Rfd1 e6 14. a3 b6 15. b4 axb4 16. axb4 Na7 $1 17. Bf1 Nb5 18. Ne5 bxc5 19. bxc5 f6 (19... Bxe5 20. dxe5 d4 $2 21. Rxa8 Bxa8 22. Bxd4 $16 {Antunes,A-Nikolaidis,I/Yerevan OL 1996}) 20. Ng4 e5 $15) 12... e6 ({There is not much difference after} 12... a5 13. a4 e6 14. Bf1 dxc4 15. bxc4 Bxf3 16. exf3 e5 17. dxe5 Qxd2 18. Bxd2 Nxe5 19. Kg2 Nd7 20. Ra3 Nc5 21. Be3 b6 22. Bxc5 bxc5 23. Rb3 Rfb8 24. Rb5 Bd4 25. Rdb1 Rxb5 26. Rxb5 Re8 27. Rxa5 Re1 28. Ra7 Ra1 29. Be2 Ra2 30. Kf1 Ra1+ 31. Kg2 Ra2 {½-½ Schroll,G-Kindermann,S/Vienna 1991}) 13. Rac1 a5 ({Although the text-move is a useful one, Black has successfully tried to live without it:} 13... Qd7 14. e3 Rad8 15. Qe2 Qe7 16. Bh3 dxc4 17. bxc4 Bxf3 18. Qxf3 e5 19. dxe5 Bxe5 20. Be1 Qa3 21. Qe2 Rxd1 22. Rxd1 Rd8 23. Rxd8+ Nxd8 $11 {Mchedlishvili,M-Mamedyarov,S/Batumi 2001}) (13... f5 14. Ne5 Bxg2 $6 (14... Nxe5 15. dxe5 Bxg2 16. Kxg2 c6 $11) 15. Nxc6 bxc6 16. Kxg2 f4 17. f3 Bh6 18. Bb4 Rf6 19. Rc2 $14 {Huebner,R-Smirin,I/Istanbul OL 2000}) 14. Ne5 Nxe5 15. dxe5 ({Also equal is} 15. Bxe4 Nxc4 16. bxc4 dxe4 17. Qe3 f5 18. f3 Qd7 19. fxe4 Qa4 $11) 15... Bxg2 16. Kxg2 c6 17. Qe3 Qc7 18. c5 Rae8 19. Qg5 Ra8 20. Bd4 Qd8 21. Qxd8 Rfxd8 22. f4 Kf8 23. Rc3 Ke7 24. Re3 Rf8 25. Rdd3 f6 26. exf6+ Bxf6 27. Bxf6+ Rxf6 28. Re5 (28. Rd4 h6 29. h4 Rff8 30. Ra4 h5 31. Re5 Rfb8 {and Black is ready for the second breakthrough.}) 28... Rf5 29. Rxf5 ({I do not really like this. White should go on with} 29. Rd4 Rxe5 30. fxe5 Rf8 31. e4 (31. Rf4 Rf5) 31... Kd7 {where he can put up an equal fight.}) 29... gxf5 30. Rd4 Kd7 31. Kf3 Kc7 32. g4 fxg4+ 33. Kxg4 Rg8+ 34. Kf3 b6 35. cxb6+ Kxb6 36. e4 (36. Rd1 a4 {.}) 36... Rg1 37. exd5 cxd5 38. Kf2 Ra1 39. Ra4 Rh1 40. Kg2 Rc1 41. Kf3 Rc2 42. h4 (42. h3 {is a better try, although Black still holds the advantage after} Rd2 {.}) 42... h5 43. Ke3 (43. Kg3 Rc7 44. Kf3 Rg7 $17 {.}) 43... Rc1 44. Rd4 Kc5 45. Ra4 Kb5 46. Rd4 Rc3+ 47. Kd2 Rh3 48. f5 Kc5 49. Ra4 exf5 50. Rxa5+ Kd4 51. b4 Rh2+ 52. Ke1 f4 53. b5 Rb2 54. Ra4+ (54. a4 Ke3 55. Kd1 f3 {.}) 54... Ke3 55. Ra3+ Ke4 56. Ra4+ (56. Rb3 Rxb3 (56... Rxa2 57. b6 Ra8 58. b7 Rb8 59. Kf2) 57. axb3 Ke5 58. Kf2 d4 $19 {.}) 56... d4 57. Ra8 Rxb5 58. Re8+ Kf3 59. a4 Ra5 60. Rh8 Kg3 (60... Kg4 61. Rg8+ {0-1 (74) Gerber,R (2360)-Grivas,E (2460) Cannes 1995 CBM 122 [Grivas,Efstratios]}) 61. Rg8+ Kxh4 62. Kf2 Rxa4 63. Kf3 Kh3 64. Kxf4 h4 65. Ke4 Kh2 66. Rb8 h3 67. Rb2+ Kg3 68. Rb3+ Kg4 (68... d3+ 69. Kxd3 h2 {.}) 69. Rb2 Ra3 70. Kxd4 Kg3 71. Rb8 h2 72. Rg8+ Kf2 73. Rf8+ Kg2 74. Rg8+ Rg3 0-1


