1. d4 Nf6 2. Nf3 g6 3. g3 Bg7 4. Bg2 O-O 5. c4 d6 6. O-O Nc6 7. Nc3 Bf5 8. d5 Na5 9. Nd4 Bd7 {(D) } (9... Nxc4 $6 {seems to be pleasant for White:} 10. Nxf5 gxf5 11. Qd3 Ne5 (11... Nb6 12. Qxf5 Qc8 13. Qc2 Qg4 14. h3 Qg6 15. Qb3 $14 {Kirton,D-Rasmussen,B/Manitoba 1991}) 12. Qxf5 c6 13. dxc6 bxc6 14. Ne4 e6 15. Nxf6+ Qxf6 16. Qc2 Rab8 17. Rb1 c5 18. h3 Rb6 19. Qa4 $14 {Noerby,P-Hvenekilde,J/Copenhagen 1968}) 10. Qd3 (10. b3 {is the alternative option.}) 10... c5 11. dxc6 ({This cannot be called an ambitious try for White.} 11. Nc2 a6 12. b3 {transposes to 10.b3}) 11... Nxc6 ({Playable is the other option:} 11... bxc6 12. Bd2 (12. Rb1 Rc8 13. e4 Ng4 14. b3 Ne5 15. Qd1 c5 16. Nde2 Nac6 17. f4 Ng4 18. h3 Nf6 19. Be3 Qa5 $13 {Rodman,F-Timoscenko,G/Ljubljana 2003}) (12. b4 $6 c5 $1 13. Bxa8 Qxa8 14. bxc5 dxc5 15. Nf3 Bf5 $17) 12... Rb8 13. b3 c5 14. Nc2 Nc6 15. e4 Nb4 16. Nxb4 cxb4 17. Ne2 Ng4 18. Rad1 a5 19. h3 Ne5 20. Qc2 Qc8 $13 {Roeber,B-Kurz,A/Germany 1995 and it probably should be tested in practice more often, as it gives Black an equal chance of winning in the coming middlegame.}) 12. b3 ({White usually tries} 12. Nxc6 bxc6 (12... Bxc6 13. e4 a5 14. Rb1 Nd7 15. Be3 Nc5 $11 {Almeida Saenz,A-Seeman,T/Mallorca 2004}) 13. h3 (13. Bd2 Rb8 14. b3 d5 15. cxd5 cxd5 16. Bf4 Rc8 17. Be5 e6 18. Rac1 Qb6 19. Qd4 Qxd4 20. Bxd4 Ng4 21. Bxg7 Kxg7 $11 {Stuhlik,M-Timoscenko,G/Oberwart 2002}) 13... Rb8 14. Rb1 Qc8 15. Kh2 Be6 16. Bf4 Rb4 17. b3 d5 18. cxd5 cxd5 19. Rbe1 Qd7 (19... Qxc3 $5 20. Qxc3 Ng4+ 21. hxg4 Bxc3 22. Rc1 d4 23. g5 Rc8) 20. Na4 Bf5 21. Qd2 a5 22. Nc5 Qa7 {½-½ Miralles,G-Piket,J/Lyon 1990}) 12... Nxd4 13. Qxd4 Bc6 14. Bb2 (14. Bxc6 $6 bxc6 15. Bb2 Qd7 $15) 14... Ne4 15. Qd3 Nxc3 16. Bxc3 Bxc3 17. Qxc3 Rc8 18. Rac1 Bxg2 19. Kxg2 Rc5 20. Qe3 Qc7 {An equal endgame has arisen. Black tried to win it (!) but in vain, as White held it with precise (and not too difficult) efforts.} 21. Rfd1 b6 22. Rd5 Qc6 23. Qf3 Rc8 24. Rcd1 a6 25. h4 Rxd5 26. Qxd5 Qxd5+ 27. Rxd5 Rc6 28. Kf3 h5 29. e4 e6 30. Rd2 Kf8 31. Ke3 Ke7 32. Kd3 f5 33. f3 Rc8 34. Rc2 Kd7 35. b4 Kc6 36. a4 Rf8 37. f4 fxe4+ 38. Kxe4 Rf5 39. b5+ Kc7 40. g4 hxg4 41. Rg2 Rc5 42. Kd4 d5 43. cxd5 Rxd5+ 44. Ke4 axb5 45. axb5 Rxb5 46. Rxg4 Rh5 47. Rxg6 Kd6 48. Kf3 Rxh4 49. f5 Ke5 50. Rxe6+ Kxf5 51. Rxb6 1/2-1/2


