1. d4 Nf6 2. Nf3 g6 3. g3 Bg7 4. Bg2 O-O 5. O-O d6 6. a4 c6 7. a5 {This is my suggested continuation.} Na6 ({Although this line is quite acceptable for Black, some other lines should be mentioned too: a)} 7... Qc7 8. Nc3 Nbd7 (8... e5 9. e4 Na6 10. h3 Re8 11. Re1 $14 {Kirov,N-Dochev,D/Elenite 1993}) 9. e4 e5 10. h3 Rb8 11. Be3 b5 12. axb6 axb6 13. d5 (13. dxe5 {½-½ Malaniuk,V-Gallagher,J/Hamburg 1995}) 13... Bb7 14. Nd2 b5 15. dxc6 Bxc6 16. Ra7 Rb7 17. Rxb7 Qxb7 18. Nb3 (18. b4 Nb6 19. Qb1 Rc8 $13 {Van der Weide,K-Kasimdzhanov,R/Groningen 1997}) 18... b4 19. Na5 (19. Nd5 Nxd5 20. exd5 Bb5 21. Re1 Ra8 $13 {Rashkovsky,N-Fedorov,V/Forli 1992}) 19... Qa8 20. Nxc6 Qxc6 (20... bxc3 21. Ne7+ Kh8 22. bxc3 $14) 21. Na2 Rb8 22. Bd2 b3 23. Nc3 Nc5 24. Re1 $14) ({b)} 7... Bf5 8. Nc3) ({c)} 7... Ne4 8. c4 Qe8 9. Nbd2 Nxd2 10. Bxd2 Na6 11. e4 Bg4 12. Be3 Qc8 13. Qd2 Bh3 14. Bh6 Bxg2 15. Kxg2 Qe6 16. Bxg7 Kxg7 17. Qc3 Kg8 18. Rae1 $14 {Romanishin,O-Khairallah,F/Paris 2004}) 8. Nc3 ({I think that} 8. Nbd2 {is more "ambitious" and should be preferred:} d5 9. c3 Bf5 10. Re1 Nc7 11. Ne5 Nd7 12. Nxd7 Qxd7 13. e4 Be6 14. Qe2 $14 {Nikolaidis,I-Tzermiadianos,A/Corfu 1995}) 8... d5 (8... Bf5 9. Nh4 {transposes.} Bd7 10. e4 e5 11. Nf3 Re8 12. Re1 b5 13. axb6 axb6 14. Bg5 h6 15. Bxf6 Bxf6 16. dxe5 dxe5 17. Qd6 (17. Qd2 $6 $11 {Kengis,E-Dydyshko,V/Katowice 1993}) 17... Kg7 18. Red1 Re7 19. h4 (19. Na4 Qb8) 19... Qc7 20. Qxc7 Nxc7 21. Rxa8 Nxa8 22. Ra1 Re8 23. Ra7 $14) 9. Bf4 Bf5 10. Be5 $5 Qd7 11. Na4 Bh6 $1 {A good move, which allows Black full equality.} 12. Bxf6 exf6 13. e3 Rfe8 14. Qe2 Bf8 15. c3 Bg4 $1 $11 16. Qd3 Bf5 17. Qe2 Bg4 18. Qd3 Bf5 1/2-1/2


