1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Qb6 5. Nb3 Nf6 6. Nc3 e6 7. Qe2 Bb4 8. Bd2 O-O 9. a3 Be7 10. O-O-O d5 $5 $146 (10... d6 11. g4 a6 12. g5 Nd7 13. h4 Qc7 14. f4 $40 {didn't end up well for black in a game Anand-Kramnik, Mainz (blitz) 2001}) 11. Be3 Qc7 12. exd5 Nxd5 13. Nxd5 exd5 14. g4 $5 {[%cal Gg4f5,Gg4g5]} (14. g3 Be6 15. Bg2 Rfd8 16. Nd4 Bf6 $13) 14... Rd8 (14... Be6 $6 15. f4 $36) 15. Bg2 Be6 16. Kb1 Rac8 17. f4 (17. h3 $142 $5 $14 {[%cal Yf2f4]}) 17... d4 18. Bc1 (18. Nxd4 Nxd4 19. Rxd4 Rxd4 20. Bxd4 Qxf4 $11) 18... d3 $1 {black immediately takes a chance to change the type of a position} (18... Bf6 $143 19. f5 Bxb3 20. cxb3 $16 {[%cal Yg2e4,Yg4g5]}) 19. Rxd3 Rxd3 20. Qxd3 Bxg4 21. Be4 g6 22. f5 Qd6 $1 (22... Bf6 23. Rg1 Ne5 24. Qf1 $1 $40 {[%csl Rf6][%cal Yh2h3]}) (22... Ne5 23. Qg3 $40) 23. Qc4 gxf5 24. Rg1 $2 (24. Bd5 $142 Rf8 (24... Kh8 25. Bxf7 (25. Bf4 b5 $1) 25... Bf6 $13) 25. Bf4 b5 (25... Ne5 $2 26. Qd4 Bf6 27. Re1 $18) 26. Qxb5 Qxf4 27. Qxc6 $13) 24... Qxh2 25. Rh1 Qc7 $1 $17 (25... Qd6 $2 26. Bd5 Kh8 27. Rh6 $40) 26. Bd5 Ne5 27. Qf4 h5 $1 {with such a pawn "castle" black has nothing to be worry about} (27... Qxc2+ $2 28. Ka2 $40) 28. Nd4 Bf6 29. Rg1 Bg7 $138 30. Rg2 Ng6 31. Qd2 a6 $2 (31... Rd8 32. Nb5 Qe5 33. c4 (33. Bxf7+ Kxf7 34. Qxd8 Qxb5 $19) 33... a6 $19) 32. Nf3 Ne7 33. Bb3 Rd8 $4 (33... Bxf3 $1 34. Rxg7+ Kxg7 35. Qh6+ Kg8 36. Qg5+ (36. Bg5 Nd5 $1 37. Bxd5 Qxc2+ 38. Ka1 Qd1+ $19 {and white king is mated instead of his black opponent}) 36... Kf8 37. Qf6 Ng6 $19) 34. Qf2 Rd1 35. c3 Rd7 $6 (35... Rxc1+ $5 {was probably a last chance to keep an advantage} 36. Kxc1 Qf4+ 37. Nd2 Qxf2 38. Rxf2 h4 $15) 36. Ng5 Nd5 37. Nxf7 $1 $11 Kxf7 38. Rxg4 hxg4 39. Qxf5+ Ke8 40. Bxd5 Qd6 (40... Qe5 41. Qg6+ Kd8 42. Be6 $11) 41. Be6 Qd3+ 1/2-1/2


