1. Nf3 Nf6 2. c4 g6 3. g3 Bg7 4. Bg2 O-O 5. O-O d6 6. d4 Nc6 7. Nc3 Bf5 8. d5 Na5 9. Nd4 Bd7 10. Qd3 c5 11. Nc2 a6 12. Rb1 Qc7 13. Bd2 Rab8 14. h3 b5 15. b3 e6 $6 16. dxe6 $1 Bxe6 {(D) } 17. Bf4 $1 {This normal move questions the validity of 15...e6?!} Rfd8 $6 ({Maybe Black is forced to accept a worse endgame with} 17... bxc4 $5 18. Qxd6 Qxd6 (18... Qa7 19. Qc7 $1 Nb7 20. bxc4) 19. Bxd6 cxb3 20. axb3 Rxb3 21. Rxb3 Nxb3 22. Bxf8 Kxf8 23. Rd1 $14) 18. Ne3 $6 ({Much stronger was} 18. cxb5 $1 c4 19. bxc4 Bxc4 20. Qd2 axb5 21. Rfd1 $16) 18... Qd7 $2 ({Bad was also} 18... Nh5 19. Bg5 f6 20. Ned5 Qd7 21. Bd2 bxc4 22. bxc4 Rxb1 23. Rxb1 Bxh3 24. Bxh3 Qxh3 25. Rb6 $16) ({but Black could gain equal chances with} 18... Nc6 $1 19. Ned5 Bxd5 20. Nxd5 Nxd5 21. Qxd5 Nb4 (21... Nd4 $5) 22. Qd2 Qa5 23. Rfd1 Be5 $1 $13) 19. g4 $1 bxc4 20. bxc4 $16 Rb4 21. Rxb4 cxb4 22. Ncd5 Bxd5 $6 (22... Nc6 23. Rd1 Qc8 24. a3 a5 25. axb4 axb4 26. Qb3 $16) 23. cxd5 Qb7 24. Rb1 Qb6 25. Nc2 Nd7 26. Rxb4 $18 Qc7 27. Nd4 (27. Qxa6 $1 Qxc2 28. Qxa5 Rc8 29. Qa4 $18) 27... Nc5 28. Qd1 Re8 29. Nc6 Nab7 30. Bf3 Nd7 31. Qc2 Nbc5 32. Rc4 Ne5 33. Bxe5 Bxe5 34. e3 Bf6 35. Kg2 Kg7 36. Rf4 Be5 37. Rb4 Bf6 38. a4 h6 39. a5 Nb7 40. Qa4 Nc5 41. Qc2 Nb7 42. Qa2 Nc5 43. Qc4 Ra8 44. Rb1 Qc8 45. Be2 Qc7 (45... Qd7 46. Bd3 {1-0 (58) Jirovsky,M (2450)-Grivas,E (2489) Germany 2001 CBM 122 [Grivas,Efstratios]}) 46. Bd3 Qc8 47. Bc2 Qd7 48. f4 Qc7 49. Rb6 Nb7 50. Qb4 Nd8 51. Bb3 Nxc6 52. dxc6 Qe7 53. e4 Rf8 54. Rb7 Qe8 55. Qc4 g5 56. c7 gxf4 57. Rb8 f3+ 58. Kxf3 1-0


